			{
				"id": "music:29-songs-for-29-days-february-2016",
				"slug": "29-songs-for-29-days-february-2016",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "29 Songs for 29 Days [February 2016]",
					"featured_image": {
						"id": "",
						"provider": "external",
						"src": "https://steelwagstaff.info/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/24700242579_9f59685597_z.jpg"
					},
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "k5",
							"style": "normal",
							"markDefs": [],
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "k0",
									"text": "Despite having a extra 24 hours provided by a glorious leap day, this past February wasn't the most musically adventurous of months for me. I didn't listen a ton of new music, but did manage to scrape together 29 tracks I listened to and enjoyed in the month (one for each day, I suppose). Favorites from the month included Joseph Arthur's ",
									"marks": []
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "k1",
									"text": "Lou",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "k2",
									"text": " [a record of Lou Reed covers], Little Dragon, Sylvan Esso (I finally gave the full record an attentive listen), The Secret Sisters, and Quantic (especially his ",
									"marks": []
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "k3",
									"text": "Look Around the Corner",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "k4",
									"text": " record with Alice Russell). Enjoy!",
									"marks": []
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "k7",
							"style": "normal",
							"markDefs": [],
							"children": [
								{
