			{
				"id": "music:50-tracks-may-2016",
				"slug": "50-tracks-may-2016",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "50 Tracks [May 2016]",
					"featured_image": {
						"id": "",
						"provider": "external",
						"src": "https://steelwagstaff.info/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Ceremony-0101.jpg"
					},
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "k1",
							"style": "normal",
							"markDefs": [],
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "k0",
									"text": "Here are 50 songs that I listened to and enjoyed in May 2016. It was a pretty average month for me, musically, but with some fun discoveries. I really liked Cicada Rhythm (a southern folk duo who sound like The Tallest Man on Earth with cello added--beautiful combination), Connie Converse (an almost unknown 1950s singer-songwriter with a fascinating, tragic story), Cotton Jones (indie folk band from Maryland), and The Memories (a couple of stoner bros from Portland whose song \"You Need A Big Man\" is both ridiculous and feels like the kind of 1 minute long Safety Dance-inspired novelty song everybody needs to start off their summer right).",
									"marks": []
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "k3",
							"style": "normal",
							"markDefs": [],
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "k2",
									"text": "https://open.spotify.com/user/steelwagstaff/playlist/1XBeUhhwZt0vtm89xO1flO",
									"marks": []
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "music:100-songs-june-2016",
				"slug": "100-songs-june-2016",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "100 Songs [June 2016]",
					"featured_image": {
						"id": "",
						"provider": "external",
						"src": "https://steelwagstaff.info/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMG_4047-copy.jpg"
					},
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "k1",
							"style": "normal",
							"markDefs": [],
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "k0",
									"text": "Here are 100 songs I listened to and enjoyed in June of 2016. It was a good summer month, in life and in music for me. Favorite discoveries included: first peoples songwriter Willie Dunn, psychadelic weirdo Jib Kidder (Sean Schuster-Craig), Donnie Trumpet & the Social Experiment, legendary blueswoman Elizabeth Cotten, Ethiopian jazz master Mulatu Astatke, Malawian musician Gasper Nali, and English folksinger Mike Cooper.",
									"marks": []
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "k3",
							"style": "normal",
							"markDefs": [],
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "k2",
									"text": "Songs I listened to most this month: Odetta's \"Hit or Miss (live)\", Kim Jung Mi's \"Haenim\", Miriam Makaba's \"Pata Pata\", The Meters' \"Hand Clapping Song\", Spirits of the Red City's \"Halfway Poem\", Rostam's \"Wood\", and Greg Holden's \"Boys in the Street\".",
									"marks": []
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "k5",
							"style": "normal",
							"markDefs": [],
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "k4",
									"text": "Enjoy!",
									"marks": []
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "k7",
							"style": "normal",
							"markDefs": [],
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "k6",
									"text": "https://open.spotify.com/user/steelwagstaff/playlist/6BLHa6uiWcWc7m059djWeo",
									"marks": []
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
