			{
				"id": "posts:my-march-2017-reading",
				"slug": "my-march-2017-reading",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "My March 2017 Reading",
					"featured_image": {
						"provider": "external",
						"id": "",
						"src": "https://steelwagstaff.info/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/6253846737_e626eed66f_b.jpg"
					},
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-2-hh5hs",
							"style": "h2",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-xwnmp",
									"text": "Books"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-6-muhy5",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-3-n6c10",
									"text": "If March had a theme for me, I suppose it would have been 'Occupy'? I may be several years late to the movement, but most of what I read this month seemed to have been written by someone involved in the Occupy protests and movements of the past half-dozen years. It's easy to love anarchists when you're only meeting them on the page in the realm of ideas, right? Well, I certainly love "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-4-davua",
									"text": "reading",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-5-ku955",
									"text": " anarchists. Here’s the best of what I read for pleasure (i.e. not for work or for my dissertation) in March of 2017."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-8-zgss4",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-7-oqn6s",
									"text": "Nonfiction"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-13-ekogm",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-9-ym6qp",
									"text": "Finally finished David Graeber's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-11-u28ip",
									"text": "Debt: The First 5000 Years",
									"marks": [
										"key-10-rbzeh",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-12-ulgfz",
									"text": ". One of the best books I've read in recent memory. It took me several months, but was well worth every hour spent on it."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-10-rbzeh",
									"href": "https://www.mhpbooks.com/books/debt/",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-20-ezfn5",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-14-loob5",
									"text": "After finishing "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-15-259tq",
									"text": "Debt",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-16-16h9e",
									"text": " I pretty much immediately read two of Graeber's other books. The first one I tackled was "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-18-x6may",
									"text": "The Utopia of Rules: On Technology, Stupidity, and the Secret Joys of Bureaucracy",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-17-570z0"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-19-nqw3p",
									"text": ". Smart, funny, and insightful, with a strong anarchist slant and a number of creative readings of many of the ubiquitous cultural and political structures that many of us love to hate."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-17-570z0",
									"href": "https://www.mhpbooks.com/books/the-utopia-of-rules/",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-28-buspu",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-21-yckjr",
									"text": "I also read Graeber's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-23-w4236",
									"text": "The Democracy Project: A History, A Crisis, A Movement",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-22-qd4as"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-24-nympq",
									"text": ". Far more pragmatic and anecdotal than the previous two books, with a number of nostalgia-tinged recastings of Occupy's 'success,' but still a worthwhile read. Turned me on to Starhawk, and her "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-26-ie7n3",
									"text": "writings on empowerment, group facilitation, and productive 'consensus-driven' meetings",
									"marks": [
										"key-25-ib6sb"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-27-5jn8n",
									"text": ", which was a fortuitous discovery."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-22-qd4as",
									"href": "http://www.randomhousebooks.com/books/220295/",
									"blank": true
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-25-ib6sb",
									"href": "http://starhawk.org/writing/books/the-empowerment-manual/",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-36-4nkft",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-29-13v8k",
									"text": "Cathy O'Neil's terrific "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
