									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-20-ns2z3",
									"text": "The soundproof audio studio where I typically record episodes of our show (I come in late at night). Photo by my coworker "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-22-tvo7i",
									"text": "David Macasaet",
									"marks": [
										"key-21-mk2bs"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-23-eex6x",
									"text": ".[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-24-ykeef",
									"text": "Here’s how I’ve been recording podcasts on my mac laptop. I go into a quiet, soundproofed space (here are some tips on "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-26-e1pf4",
									"text": "soundproofing",
									"marks": [
										"key-25-72zhu"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-27-q4y1z",
									"text": " and "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-29-q75um",
									"text": "improving the acoustics",
									"marks": [
										"key-28-x7tes"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-30-ft640",
									"text": " of your own space), call Dave and our guest(s) using Google Hangouts, and record the audio from our video call. After the call ends, I edit the recording, add bumper music, normalize and compress the audio, and export as a 64kbs .mp3 file with the desired metadata. Then I upload the file to my server using an FTP client, write a blog post about the episode, link to the uploaded file (using the free "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-32-vof0g",
									"text": "PowerPress podcasting plugin",
									"marks": [
										"key-31-s8a2i"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-33-lpixx",
									"text": " for WordPress) and schedule publication for the desired date/time. When it publishes, our RSS feed is updated, which updates the iTunes and Stitcher podcast listings, and we’ve set up WordPress to automatically post to our show’s "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-35-0aw65",
									"text": "pretty basic Facebook page",
									"marks": [
										"key-34-ozj58"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-36-b4zgx",
									"text": ". The whole process rarely takes me more 4–5 hours per episode, including recording time."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-21-mk2bs",
									"href": "http://www.davidmacasaet.com/",
									"blank": true
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-25-72zhu",
									"href": "http://incomeschool.com/sound-proof-podcast-room/",
									"blank": true
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-28-x7tes",
									"href": "http://incomeschool.com/podcast-acoustics-room/",
									"blank": true
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-31-s8a2i",
									"href": "https://wordpress.org/plugins/powerpress/",
									"blank": true
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-34-ozj58",
									"href": "https://www.facebook.com/offthechainpodcast/",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-39-698lt",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-38-yfq5n",
									"text": "(FREE) STUFF TO DOWNLOAD:",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-49-yor7y",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-41-b0v4f",
									"text": "LineIn",
									"marks": [
										"key-40-x75a0"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-42-v10o2",
									"text": ": A free, lightweight software application from a company called Rogue Ameoba for Mac OS. This lets you play your own microphone through to your audio input channel — it’s a super simple application, and literally consists of a single button, but it’s pretty important. It appears they now have a better product called "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-44-lzkft",
									"text": "SoundSource",
									"marks": [
										"key-43-l4lfz"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-45-nhhf7",
									"text": " ("
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
