				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "My November 2016 Reading",
					"featured_image": {
						"provider": "external",
						"id": "",
						"src": "https://steelwagstaff.info/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/liwf2uhxs0q-annie-spratt.jpg"
					},
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-2-c19ze",
							"style": "h2",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-qtgo4",
									"text": "Books"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-5-k9bnf",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-3-le1f2",
									"text": "My reading pace slowed a bit in November (the US elections and their sad aftermath have provided me with lots of avenues for distraction and worry), but I still managed to keep up my love affair with books, though I picked a fair amount of duds this month. The poetry and fiction were great, but the nonfiction didn't really light a spark in me. I did read a fair amount of graphic work this month, which was mostly new for me, though it was pretty hit and miss.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-4-uyisx",
									"text": "Outside of the reading I’ve been doing for my dissertation and my work, here’s a list of the books I read for pleasure/self-education in November 2016:"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-7-7d35t",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-6-0eduh",
									"text": "Poetry"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-12-ns45a",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-8-kjbwm",
									"text": "Catherine Jagoe’s "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-10-h8y0k",
									"text": "Bloodroot",
									"marks": [
										"key-9-aa031",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-11-p6baa",
									"text": " (a new poetry collection by a friend). The book had several outstanding poems about making one's home in a strange land, and a very impressive, moving section about pregnancy and motherhood."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-9-aa031",
									"href": "http://www.settlementhouse.us/bloodroot",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-17-cx6ep",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-13-4dqzv",
									"text": "Robert Lax's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-15-dmpxj",
									"text": "A Thing That Is",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-14-9wxo2"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-16-xz039",
									"text": ". Minimalist, contemplative poetry from a tremendously interesting human being."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-14-9wxo2",
									"href": "https://www.amazon.com/Thing-That-New-Poems/dp/0879518855",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-21-nb8l2",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-19-dcbky",
									"text": "Archaic Greek Poetry: An Anthology",
									"marks": [
										"key-18-bksmm",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-20-dax74",
									"text": ", edited by Barbara Hughes Foster."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-18-bksmm",
									"href": "https://uwpress.wisc.edu/books/0047.htm",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-25-t7fph",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-23-i7vf3",
									"text": "The Collected Poems of Kenneth Fearing",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-22-ths52"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-24-nfijk",
									"text": ". Fearing was a prominent leftist writer in the 1930s. In the late 1920s he attended the UW-Madison where he lived with the poet Carl Rakosi and was a lover of Margery Latimer's. His poems are angry, cynical, and fairly iconoclastic for their time--it seems me that they anticipate much that would be later developed by American counter-culture writers in the late 1950s and 60s."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-22-ths52",
									"href": "http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/284200",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-27-ipo3u",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-26-ww13f",
									"text": "Fiction"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-32-0nh4e",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-28-xo3b1",
									"text": "Jhumpa Lahiri’s short story collection "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-30-tlc55",
									"text": "Interpreter of Maladies",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-29-pmpjq"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-31-mnv34",
									"text": " (a birthday gift from my friend Theresa). Highly recommended!"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-29-pmpjq",
									"href": "http://www.hmhco.com/shop/books/Interpreter-of-Maladies/9780395927205",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-34-myuvh",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-33-w8nsf",
									"text": "Non-fiction"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-39-k9z4f",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-35-mccv4",
									"text": "Alphonso Lingis' "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-37-h3w3u",
									"text": "The Community of Those Who Have Nothing In Common",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-36-2sann"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-38-2exdc",
									"text": ". A short book made up of dense, often beautiful phenomenologically-inflected reflections on community, illness, embodiment, death, etc.."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-36-2sann",
									"href": "http://www.iupress.indiana.edu/product_info.php?products_id=20723",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-44-5jw4t",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-40-qxs8e",
									"text": "Catherine Osborne's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-42-dg9vs",
									"text": "Presocratic Philosophy: A Very Short Introduction",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-41-ge6xk"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-43-bqtqj",
									"text": ". Not my favorite book in the series."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-41-ge6xk",
									"href": "https://global.oup.com/academic/product/presocratic-philosophy-a-very-short-introduction-9780192840943?cc=us&lang=en&",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-49-y2gbn",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-45-lve35",
									"text": "Adam Silverstein's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-47-3b593",
									"text": "Islamic History: A Very Short Introduction",
									"marks": [
										"key-46-2pypq",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-48-fjlwo",
									"text": ". Covered a lot of ground. Very learned, but I felt that the author's ideological commitments are probably at odds with my own."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-46-2pypq",
									"href": "https://global.oup.com/academic/product/islamic-history-a-very-short-introduction-9780199545728?q=islamic%20history&lang=en&cc=us",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-54-iwrfm",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-50-mb9zr",
									"text": "Eric Tyson and Ray Brown's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-52-n36w8",
									"text": "Home Buying for Dummies",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-51-hlq1c"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-53-qky1h",
									"text": ". Not the most engrossing read, but I learned a lot."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-51-hlq1c",
