			{
				"id": "posts:summer-reading",
				"slug": "summer-reading",
				"status": "draft",
				"data": {
					"title": "Summer Reading",
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-2-jgmm1",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-a36op",
									"text": "I decided this summer to rededicate myself to reading more books, in the place of the longform journalism that had become habitual to me. I even went to the public library and checked out print copies of books, though I ended up reading just as much on my iPad (if not more) as I did on paper. Here's a partial list of what I read this summer and would recommend to others:"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-4-2hcyh",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-3-zrarb",
									"text": "Finance"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-6-kirrf",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-5-9ps90",
									"text": "I've recently tried to educate myself about investment (thinking about retirement and saving for our young son's education). I've become a strong advocate of passive investing (well-constructed index funds), and very much have a bias towards high savings rates combined with a set it and forget it approach biased towards broad, longterm equity exposure. I've read half a dozen books lately that impressed me, listed in order of interest:"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-12-u9nhx",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-7-zfh6f",
									"text": "Jason Zweig's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-9-6qhna",
									"text": "Your Money and Your Brain",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-8-ky741"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-10-qbk4h",
									"text": ". ",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-11-n3ux6",
									"text": "Zweig is a longtime financial journalist and columnist at the Wall Street Journal who consistently talks sense. He strikes me as a rigorous, skeptical thinker that has great concern for consumer/investor advocacy."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-8-ky741",
									"href": "http://jasonzweig.com/project/your-money-and-your-brain/",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-33-d3n60",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-13-cvrqx",
									"text": "John Bogle's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-15-rzyfi",
									"text": "Common Sense on Mutual Funds: Updated 10th Anniversary Edition",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-14-c2qr8"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-16-v13yr",
									"text": ". ",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-17-ie2r3",
									"text": "I also read Bogle's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-19-qnrii",
									"text": "Bogle On Mutual Funds: New Perspectives For The Intelligent Investor",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-18-8pzhf"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-20-18b52",
									"text": " ",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-21-2crqn",
									"text": "and his\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-23-iomk4",
									"text": "Little Book of Common Sense Investing",
									"marks": [
										"key-22-7q8d4",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-24-qdh8a",
									"text": "--it's a shorter version of essentially the same arguments. Both were excellent. Bogle was the creator (4o years ago now!) of the first index fund, and the founder and longtime chairman of the Vanguard Group, and the namesake and honorary "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-25-mwun8",
									"text": "pater familias",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-26-yck5p",
									"text": " of the "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-28-bxuar",
									"text": "Bogleheads",
									"marks": [
										"key-27-rpgqc"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-29-d2y0e",
									"text": ", an unfailingly helpful group of DIY investors with a commitment to low costs and a passive, "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-31-ffnn3",
									"text": "rational approach to investing",
									"marks": [
										"key-30-bj377"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-32-syt8h",
									"text": "."
								}
