			{
				"id": "posts:best-of-what-i-read-in-march-2015",
				"slug": "best-of-what-i-read-in-march-2015",
				"status": "draft",
				"data": {
					"title": "Best of What I Read in March 2015",
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-2-vaq1b",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-8kcu7",
									"text": "Here's a collection of the best articles (mostly longform) I read in the past month:"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-7-mrskd",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-4-pyaa2",
									"text": "Rugby Takes a Deeper Look at Concussions",
									"marks": [
										"key-3-exuu3",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-5-6jqc6",
									"text": " by EMMA STONEY",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-6-svqwa",
									"text": "WELLINGTON — Steve Devine knows all too well how debilitating the long-term effects of concussions can be.  The 35-year-old former New Zealand, Blues and Auckland scrum-half was forced to retire from rugby in 2007 because of repeated concussions.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-3-exuu3",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/24/sports/rugby/24iht-rugby24.html?src=recg&pagewanted=all"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-12-8y908",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-9-fzwxl",
									"text": "What’s a Monkey to Do in Tampa?",
									"marks": [
										"key-8-3jubd",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-10-6bnom",
									"text": " by JON MOOALLEM",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-11-zmm2y",
									"text": "The monkey appeared behind a Bennigan’s. The Bennigan’s was one in a row of free-standing, fast-casual joints in Clearwater, Fla., just outside Tampa, that also includes a Panda Express and a Chipotle.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-8-3jubd",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/26/magazine/tampa-monkey.html?_r=1&pagewanted=all"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-17-7d2jj",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-14-7dk3i",
									"text": "Greg Ousley Is Sorry for Killing His Parents. Is That Enough?",
									"marks": [
										"key-13-q57bv",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-15-khe83",
									"text": " by Scott Anderson",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-16-tl6yp",
									"text": "Greg Ousley, who is serving a 60-year sentence for murdering his parents at age 14.  For 19 years, Greg Ousley has sought to make sense of the event that has haunted and dictated his life, but the answer, if such a simple thing exists, has remained forever beyond his grasp.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-13-q57bv",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/22/magazine/greg-ousley-is-sorry-for-killing-his-parents-is-that-enough.html?_r=1&smid=fb-share&pagewanted=all"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-22-xi3on",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-19-1z0w7",
									"text": "Planet of the apes",
									"marks": [
										"key-18-t3pui",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-20-zux9m",
									"text": " by Stephen Cave",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-21-6pgt4",
									"text": "Once upon a time, there was an ape that stood up. Why it stood up nobody knows, but once upright it found it could use its hands to fashion tools from sticks and stones. So it stayed standing up. And once it decided to stay standing up, its brain started to grow.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-18-t3pui",
									"href": "http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/b0f049bc-e553-11e1-b758-00144feab49a.html#axzz23ssL9tLw"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-27-g1zm5",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-24-r5bth",
									"text": "Me Translate Funny One Day",
									"marks": [
										"key-23-ct1zg",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-25-6cdxs",
									"text": " by Jascha Hoffman",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-26-6mve4",
									"text": "Essay Me Translate Funny One Day Published: October 19, 2012          Last year, an Australian news anchor who was interviewing the Dalai Lama with the aid of an interpreter opened the exchange with a joke: “The Dalai Lama walks into a pizza shop and says, ‘Can you make me one with every",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
