								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-209-fx2ur",
									"text": "Andrew Pole had just started working as a statistician for Target in 2002, when two colleagues from the marketing department stopped by his desk to ask an odd question: “If we wanted to figure out if a customer is pregnant, even if she didn’t want us to know, can you do that? ”",
