									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-243-w4wpu",
									"text": " by James Somers",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-244-7c5hk",
									"text": "Douglas Hofstadter, the Pulitzer Prize–winning author of Gödel, Escher, Bach, thinks we've lost sight of what artificial intelligence really means. His stubborn quest to replicate the human mind. “It depends on what you mean by artificial intelligence.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
