									"href": "http://www.npr.org/blogs/health/2014/01/01/258674011/editing-your-lifes-stories-can-create-happier-endings?utm_content=socialflow&utm_campaign=nprfacebook&utm_source=npr&utm_medium=facebook"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-274-9bapi",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-271-ivxy5",
									"text": "Is the United States a ‘Racial Democracy’?",
									"marks": [
										"key-270-w3lx0",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-272-1uw8v",
									"text": " by JASON STANLEY, VESLA WEAVER",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-273-mq8wo",
									"text": "Plato’s “Republic” is the wellspring from which all subsequent Western philosophy flows, and political philosophy is no exception. According to Plato, liberty is democracy’s greatest good; it is that which “in a democratic city you will hear … is the most precious of all possessions.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
