								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-282-jxnh7",
									"text": " by Emily Alpert Reyes",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-283-hnxxs",
									"text": "Brent Kroeger pores over nasty online comments about stay-at-home dads, wondering if his friends think those things about him. The Rowland Heights father remembers high school classmates laughing when he said he wanted to be a \"house husband.\" He avoids mentioning it on Facebook.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-280-lrjxt",
									"href": "http://www.latimes.com/local/la-me-one-way-gender-revolution-20131227,0,7169949.story?utm_content=buffer47419&utm_source=buffer&utm_medium=twitter&utm_campaign=Buffer#axzz2ogYAQYl0"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-289-6ash4",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-286-49j7l",
									"text": "Peace in our time",
									"marks": [
										"key-285-4oxf9",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-287-bogxa",
									"text": " by Simon Kuper",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-288-doj36",
									"text": "When war broke out in August 1914, crowds in Trafalgar Square cheered. In Germany, even the liberal novelist Thomas Mann exulted, “War! We felt a cleansing, a liberation.” The “world of peace” had bored him.  His words show how far we have come since.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-285-4oxf9",
									"href": "http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/2177ebce-7e44-11e3-b409-00144feabdc0.html?ftcamp=published_links%2Frss%2Flife-arts_simon-kuper%2Ffeed%2F%2Fproduct"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-294-2l0ix",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-291-300bv",
									"text": "Another Word",
									"marks": [
										"key-290-8r0vk",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-292-vsnib",
									"text": " by Rebecca Steffy Couch",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-293-6lmaa",
									"text": "Rebecca is in her third year teaching for the UW-Madison Writing Center, and she is writing a dissertation on recent American poetics through the lens of community discourse and spatial theory in the English Literary Studies program at UW-Madison.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-290-8r0vk",
									"href": "http://writing.wisc.edu/blog/?p=4422"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-299-bc4m3",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-296-siu21",
									"text": "Love this characterization of how scarcity affects creativity",
									"marks": [
										"key-295-prcd1",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-297-s6bv7",
									"text": " by Patrick",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-298-7qoke",
									"text": "Adam Gopnik writes in a recent New Yorker about two new books, one about Duke Ellington and the other about the Beatles. The whole piece, as with almost any Gopnik article, is wonderfully thoughtful and engaging, capturing complex arguments with ease.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-295-prcd1",
									"href": "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/GreetingsFromEvanstonIll/~3/sjGUpBmXCeg/love-this-characterization-of-how-scarcity-affects-creativity.html"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-304-drp8j",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-301-855hq",
									"text": "How to save France",
									"marks": [
										"key-300-ht41c",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-302-uzwra",
									"text": " by Simon Kuper",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-303-f4nh1",
									"text": "France has lots going for it. I’ve been here 12 years, and it’s a beautiful, fairly well-off country with good food and a life expectancy of 82. Yet as the therapists would say, it’s “not in a good place right now”.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-300-ht41c",
									"href": "http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/9fc2831e-8ebf-11e3-b6f1-00144feab7de.html?ftcamp=published_links%2Frss%2Flife-arts_simon-kuper%2Ffeed%2F%2Fproduct"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-308-xxdgg",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-306-t302x",
									"text": "Driven to act: How I got through racial hazing and how what I learned can help Madison",
									"marks": [
										"key-305-jiuz3",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-307-j1oth",
									"text": "After reading Rev.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-305-jiuz3",
									"href": "http://host.madison.com/news/local/driven-to-act-how-i-got-through-racial-hazing-and/article_e7852daa-0ff1-5429-a6f2-61a41fe97970.html#ixzz2t7oRQgAC"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-313-b2szf",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-310-2e4fj",
									"text": "How to save the UK",
									"marks": [
										"key-309-vhy82",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-311-x7xt5",
									"text": " by Simon Kuper",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-312-t5ocz",
									"text": "After I wrote a column making eight suggestions to “save France” (February 8/9), many French readers accused me of “France-bashing”. Today I’m offering eight suggestions to save the UK. The French can dismiss this as Britain-bashing but, again, I’m only trying to help.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-309-vhy82",
									"href": "http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/61f9f30e-98fc-11e3-a32f-00144feab7de.html?ftcamp=published_links%2Frss%2Flife-arts_simon-kuper%2Ffeed%2F%2Fproduct"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-318-erxf8",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-315-cws5f",
									"text": "Brazil, 100 days away",
									"marks": [
										"key-314-5zaft",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-316-esp6a",
									"text": " by Wright Thompson",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-317-k6oq6",
									"text": "SAO PAULO – We landed in Brazil 102 days before the first game of the World Cup, and nobody cared. Well, we cared, because we’re from an American television network and paid to notice these things, but nobody else did.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-314-5zaft",
									"href": "http://espnfc.com/news/story/_/id/1735767/wright-thompson-100-days-out?cc=5901"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-323-mbnhd",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-320-4bs0u",
									"text": "‘The Divide,’ by Matt Taibbi",
									"marks": [
										"key-319-p9o35",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-321-r3aqp",
									"text": " by Timothy Noah",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-322-1tfcs",
									"text": "“Low-class people do low-class things.” What’s notable in this reflexive dismissal of those with modest means are not the words themselves.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-319-p9o35",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/13/books/review/the-divide-by-matt-taibbi.html?emc=edit_bk_20140411&nl=books&nlid=36318574"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-328-oa2gu",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-325-m3ltu",
									"text": "Neon Trees, The Mormon Band Who Made It Big, On Honesty",
									"marks": [
										"key-324-dtqor",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-326-wztkh",
									"text": " by NPR Staff",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-327-nyonz",
									"text": "In the audio of this story, we give an incomplete name for the band members' church. It is the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-324-dtqor",
									"href": "http://www.npr.org/2014/04/26/306866305/neon-trees-the-mormon-band-who-made-it-big-on-honesty?utm_source=facebook.com&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=npr&utm_term=nprnews&utm_content=20140426"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-333-evm67",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-330-jlbpk",
									"text": "Why Europe works",
									"marks": [
										"key-329-r8yf1",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-331-f4kju",
									"text": " by Simon Kuper",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-332-dms9h",
									"text": "Some days, I drop my children at school in Paris at 8.30am, and before noon I’m having coffee in London. This sort of experience is becoming quite normal in Europe.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-329-r8yf1",
									"href": "http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/51dd9432-db03-11e3-8273-00144feabdc0.html?ftcamp=published_links%2Frss%2Flife-arts_simon-kuper%2Ffeed%2F%2Fproduct"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-338-a3uun",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-335-ph42i",
									"text": "A portrait of Europe’s white working class",
									"marks": [
										"key-334-fwb7n",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-336-hngf7",
									"text": " by Simon Kuper",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-337-tdc0c",
									"text": "Sixty-odd years ago, May Snowden moved into the comfortable, green, working-class neighbourhood of Higher Blackley, in north Manchester. She had two sons and, after her husband died, she raised them herself. She used to know everyone in the neighbourhood.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-334-fwb7n",
									"href": "http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/4139381a-f1bb-11e3-a2da-00144feabdc0.html?ftcamp=published_links%2Frss%2Flife-arts_simon-kuper%2Ffeed%2F%2Fproduct"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-343-kvd5l",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-340-zwsqz",
									"text": "Bowe Bergdahl Faces Desertion, Misbehavior Charges",
									"marks": [
										"key-339-zluv0",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-341-wdtsa",
									"text": " by Michael Hastings",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-342-y3fjk",
									"text": "In June 2012, fearless Rolling Stone contributing editor Michael Hastings wrote the definitive first account of Bowe Bergdahl — the young American soldier who was captured by the Taliban and became the last American prisoner of war.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-339-zluv0",
									"href": "http://www.rollingstone.com/politics/news/americas-last-prisoner-of-war-20120607?print=true"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-348-xpr6k",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-345-7tbi5",
									"text": "Confessions of a Drone Warrior",
									"marks": [
										"key-344-1vym8",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-346-36pwq",
									"text": " by Matthew Power",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-347-2kn5n",
									"text": "Editor's Note: On March 10, 2014, journalist Matthew Power lost his life pursuing a story along the Nile River in Uganda. He left behind a body of work as diverse and compelling as the adventures, tragedies, and passions of his subjects.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-344-1vym8",
									"href": "http://www.gq.com/news-politics/big-issues/201311/drone-uav-pilot-assassination?printable=true"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-353-61fmr",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-350-w8iq9",
									"text": "Book review: The transformation of the world by Jurgen Osterhammel",
									"marks": [
										"key-349-e8uck",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-351-4odru",
									"text": " by Samuel Moyn",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-352-p13af",
									"text": "Stockport viaduct, 1845: faster transport connected the world in new ways.  In the imagination of historians, the 19th century once reigned supreme.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-349-e8uck",
									"href": "http://www.prospectmagazine.co.uk/magazine/book-review-the-transformation-of-the-world-by-jurgen-osterhammel"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-358-aw5ta",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-355-wya0r",
									"text": "One of a Kind",
									"marks": [
										"key-354-0sww6",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-356-nse19",
									"text": " by Seth Mnookin",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-357-p9lvs",
									"text": "Matt Might and Cristina Casanova met in the spring of 2002, as twenty-year-old undergraduates at the Georgia Institute of Technology. Cristina was an industrial-design major with an interest in philosophy; Matt was a shy computer geek obsessed with “Star Trek.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-354-0sww6",
									"href": "http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2014/07/21/one-of-a-kind-2?currentPage=all"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-363-q7lqi",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-360-3dt0e",
									"text": "Wrong Answer",
									"marks": [
										"key-359-in45v",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-361-am3p3",
									"text": " by Rachel Aviv",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-362-uk46k",
									"text": "One afternoon in the spring of 2006, Damany Lewis, a math teacher at Parks Middle School, in Atlanta, unlocked the room where standardized tests were kept.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-359-in45v",
									"href": "http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2014/07/21/wrong-answer?currentPage=all"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-368-gdooy",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-365-bhr1x",
									"text": "Why Do Americans Stink at Math?",
									"marks": [
										"key-364-94c46",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-366-je4me",
									"text": " by ELIZABETH GREEN",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-367-yd80x",
									"text": "When Akihiko Takahashi was a junior in college in 1978, he was like most of the other students at his university in suburban Tokyo. He had a vague sense of wanting to accomplish something but no clue what that something should be.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-364-94c46",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/07/27/magazine/why-do-americans-stink-at-math.html?action=click&contentCollection=Middle+East&module=MostEmailed&version=Full&region=Marginalia&src=me&pgtype=article"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-373-6n35g",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-370-ar4yl",
									"text": "Our unrealistic views of death, through a doctor’s eyes",
									"marks": [
										"key-369-t0f5p",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-371-tkwwd",
									"text": " by Craig Bowron",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-372-2kipq",
									"text": "I know where this phone call is going. I’m on the hospital wards, and a physician in the emergency room downstairs is talking to me about an elderly patient who needs to be admitted to the hospital.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-369-t0f5p",
									"href": "http://m.washingtonpost.com/opinions/our-unrealistic-views-of-death-through-a-doctors-eyes/2012/01/31/gIQAeaHpJR_story.html?tid=sm_fb"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-377-5pvop",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-375-gw7j5",
									"text": "Suzanne Sadedin's answer to What is the evolutionary benefit or purpose of having periods?",
									"marks": [
										"key-374-ypykn",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-376-jqxt0",
									"text": "I'm so glad you asked. Seriously. The answer to this question is one of the most illuminating and disturbing stories in human evolutionary biology, and almost nobody knows about it.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-374-ypykn",
									"href": "http://www.quora.com/Menstruation/What-is-the-evolutionary-benefit-or-purpose-of-having-periods/answer/Suzanne-Sadedin?srid=iwL&share=1"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-382-m6ro7",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-379-0z478",
									"text": "The People V. Football",
									"marks": [
										"key-378-nomai",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-380-qhbwq",
									"text": " by Jeanne Marie Laskas",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-381-0nhyp",
									"text": "She had no idea, back then, that he was sick. She had no idea he was losing his mind. Something neurological, the doctors are now saying, some kind of sludge blocking pathways in his brain. Would it have made a difference if she knew? Of course it would have. But you can't think like that.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-378-nomai",
									"href": "http://www.gq.com/news-politics/big-issues/201102/jeanne-marie-laskas-nfl-concussions-fred-mcneill?printable=true&currentPage=1"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-387-3y8mc",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-384-a576d",
									"text": "The Rise of Beefcake Yoga",
									"marks": [
										"key-383-foruj",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-385-67eaj",
									"text": " by Alex French",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-386-5im4k",
									"text": "A horde of screaming middle-aged wrestling fans gathered one Saturday evening in April at the Smoothie King Center in New Orleans to celebrate professional wrestling’s Hall of Fame induction ceremony.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-383-foruj",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/17/magazine/the-rise-of-beefcake-yoga.html?ref=magazine&_r=0"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-392-guk2n",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-389-m6u8e",
									"text": "Inside the Dark, Lucrative World of Consumer Debt Collection",
									"marks": [
										"key-388-38pn8",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-390-1o3vk",
									"text": " by JAKE HALPERN",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-391-b7j0t",
									"text": "One afternoon in October 2009, a former banking executive named Aaron Siegel waited impatiently in the master bedroom of a house in Buffalo that served as his office.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-388-38pn8",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2014/08/15/magazine/bad-paper-debt-collector.html?ref=magazine"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-397-z4eih",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-394-cz1qq",
									"text": "The Strange & Curious Tale of the Last True Hermit",
									"marks": [
										"key-393-2vssr",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-395-s6hrm",
									"text": " by Michael Finkel",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-396-etrjm",
									"text": "The hermit set out of camp at midnight, carrying his backpack and his bag of break-in tools, and threaded through the forest, rock to root to rock, every step memorized. Not a boot print left behind.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-393-2vssr",
									"href": "http://www.gq.com/news-politics/newsmakers/201409/the-last-true-hermit?printable=true"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-402-rtvv9",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-399-hg7z7",
									"text": "[Criticism] : The Soft-Kill Solution, by Ando Arike : Harper's Magazine",
									"marks": [
										"key-398-6bytr",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-400-g6hwh",
									"text": " by Ando Arike",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-401-913bu",
									"text": "Not long ago, viewers of CBS’s 60 Minutes were treated to an intriguing bit of political theater when, in a story called “The Pentagon’s Ray Gun,” a crowd of what seemed to be angry protesters confronted a Humvee with a sinister-looking dish antenna on its roof.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-398-6bytr",
									"href": "http://harpers.org/archive/2010/03/the-soft-kill-solution/?single=1"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-407-31hig",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-404-af7kq",
									"text": "On Bigfoot's Trail",
									"marks": [
										"key-403-wu2gj",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-405-a397c",
									"text": " by Deanna Pan",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-406-alxpx",
									"text": "You've probably seen her before. Captured in grainy 16mm Kodachrome color film, she walks upstream along a sandbar on the opposite edge of a creek. It's an easy gait, brisk yet casual. Her knees are bent; her elongated arms swing freely at her sides. In a moment suspended in time, she glances back.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-403-wu2gj",
									"href": "http://www.inlander.com/spokane/on-bigfoots-trail/Content?oid=2348065"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-412-ufl58",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-409-d2r8t",
									"text": "What Killed My Sister?",
									"marks": [
										"key-408-re4ys",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-410-8e1r1",
									"text": " by Priscilla Long",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-411-0vb48",
									"text": "Susanne Long was my sister, three years younger. She was funny and savvy. She was creative and kind and curious. She had a master’s degree, and she taught English as a second language in Washington, D.C., and later in Seattle.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-408-re4ys",
									"href": "http://theamericanscholar.org/what-killed-my-sister/#.U2Jh68S9KSO"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-416-67o7j",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-414-ey41k",
									"text": "So You Think You're Smarter Than A CIA Agent",
									"marks": [
										"key-413-cpg9r",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-415-pa35l",
									"text": "The morning I met Elaine Rich, she was sitting at the kitchen table of her small town home in suburban Maryland trying to estimate refugee flows in Syria.  Will North Korea launch a new multistage missile before May 10, 2014?",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-413-cpg9r",
									"href": "http://www.npr.org/blogs/parallels/2014/04/02/297839429/-so-you-think-youre-smarter-than-a-cia-agent?utm_source=pocket&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=pockethits"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-421-8p1im",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-418-p1y24",
									"text": "The Trip",
									"marks": [
										"key-417-0mk93",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-419-ofi6f",
									"text": " by John Whalen",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-420-okij9",
									"text": "One morning in April 1962, Cary Grant swallowed four tiny blue pills of lysergic acid diethylamide — LSD. Incredibly, it was the 58-year-old actor’s 72nd acid trip under the supervision of a psychiatrist. Grant relaxed on a plush couch and sipped coffee as the drug began to take effect.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-417-0mk93",
									"href": "http://www.laweekly.com/1998-07-09/news/the-trip/?showFullText=true"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-425-55y6m",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-423-6c375",
									"text": "Rambo's end: A shooting, a manhunt, decades of fallout",
									"marks": [
										"key-422-oalcv",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-424-3jedq",
									"text": "In the summer of 1987, police swarmed the woods around Wausau, on the hunt for a Michigan prison escapee accused of breaking into a cabin and shooting the owner. That fugitive, Steven K.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-422-oalcv",
									"href": "http://www.wausaudailyherald.com/longform/opinion/2014/09/20/rambos-end-steven-thompson-wausau-manhunt-fallout/15913911/"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-430-9cbkb",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-427-kdf4j",
									"text": "Exposing Hidden Bias at Google",
									"marks": [
										"key-426-wznhs",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-428-lkbyd",
									"text": " by FARHAD MANJOO",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-429-9d28j",
									"text": "Google, like many tech companies, is a man’s world.  Started by a pair of men, its executive team is overwhelmingly male, and its work force is dominated by men. Over all, seven out of 10 people who work at Google are male.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-426-wznhs",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/25/technology/exposing-hidden-biases-at-google-to-improve-diversity.html?emc=edit_ct_20140925&nl=technology&nlid=36318574&_r=0"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-435-rpykj",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-432-xi214",
									"text": "The Woman Who Walked 10,000 Miles (No Exaggeration) in Three Years",
									"marks": [
										"key-431-dcn1u",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-433-nbas8",
									"text": " by ELIZABETH WEIL",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-434-e6vtl",
									"text": "A hundred years ago, when Robert Falcon Scott set out for Antarctica on his Terra Nova expedition, his two primary goals were scientific discovery and reaching the geographic South Pole. Arguably, though, Scott was really chasing what contemporary observers call a sufferfest.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-431-dcn1u",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/28/magazine/the-woman-who-walked-10000-miles-no-exaggeration-in-three-years.html?ref=magazine&_r=0"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-440-b0rjb",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-437-fr0dl",
									"text": "Father of History",
									"marks": [
										"key-436-cssd5",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-438-gnp3v",
									"text": " by JOSEPH EPSTEIN",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-439-zw4wy",
									"text": "Herodotus, the first Greek and thereby the first Western historian, had bad press long before there was anything resembling a press. Aristotle referred to him as a “story-teller,” which was no honorific. What he meant was that Herodotus made things up, another word for which is “liar.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-436-cssd5",
									"href": "http://www.weeklystandard.com/articles/father-history_810879.html?nopager=1"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-445-zqqkf",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-442-mbi8q",
									"text": "Deep into Green",
									"marks": [
										"key-441-vu6vv",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-443-qmv3j",
									"text": " by Michael Gorra",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-444-m6kam",
									"text": "About twenty years ago I found myself in Washington’s National Gallery and looking for a way to slow down.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-441-vu6vv",
									"href": "http://www.nybooks.com/articles/archives/2014/sep/25/deep-green/?insrc=hpss"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-450-r2bz2",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-447-luwf2",
									"text": "The Beggars of Lakewood",
									"marks": [
										"key-446-cy98l",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-448-hj4j2",
									"text": " by MARK OPPENHEIMER",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-449-yujqt",
									"text": "Once a year, Elimelech Ehrlich travels from Jerusalem to Lakewood, N.J., with a cash box and a wireless credit-card machine.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-446-cy98l",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/19/magazine/the-beggars-of-lakewood.html?ref=magazine&_r=0"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-455-t7gyz",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-452-j4hap",
									"text": "The Master",
									"marks": [
										"key-451-znovk",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-453-bwkg3",
									"text": " by Marc Fisher",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-454-jvo9e",
									"text": "When I was in high school, at Horace Mann, in the Bronx, in the nineteen-seventies, everyone took pride in the brilliant eccentricity of our teachers.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-451-znovk",
									"href": "http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2013/04/01/130401fa_fact_fisher?currentPage=all"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-460-bxd69",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-457-cacf5",
									"text": "The Reckoning",
									"marks": [
										"key-456-b9zin",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-458-nux0u",
									"text": " by Andrew Solomon",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-459-pugdj",
									"text": "In Peter Lanza’s new house, on a secluded private road in Fairfield County, Connecticut, is an attic room overflowing with shipping crates of what he calls “the stuff.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-456-b9zin",
									"href": "http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2014/03/17/140317fa_fact_solomon?currentPage=all"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-465-pht73",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-462-lud2d",
									"text": "The Secrets of Color",
									"marks": [
										"key-461-bpf0x",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-463-rqd65",
									"text": " by Sebastian Smee",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-464-zkdqa",
									"text": "At one end of our bathtub is a demolition derby of plastic ducks, a dinosaur, and a mermaid Barbie in a formfitting pink-and-blue outfit, her bright-blond hair streaked with red and blue.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-461-bpf0x",
									"href": "http://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2014/12/the-secrets-of-color/382229/?single_page=true"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-470-c7u9c",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-467-7m1de",
									"text": "The Curious Case of Jesus’s Wife",
									"marks": [
										"key-466-mm2c4",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-468-5rh3f",
									"text": " by Joel Baden, Candida Moss",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-469-ca3h2",
									"text": "Lab tests have suggested that a papyrus scrap mentioning Jesus's wife is authentic. Why do most scholars believe it's fake? For six days in September 2012, some 300 participants came together at Sapienza University, in Rome, for the 10th International Congress of Coptic Studies.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-466-mm2c4",
									"href": "http://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2014/12/the-curious-case-of-jesuss-wife/382227/?single_page=true"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-475-lqsf6",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-472-quuah",
									"text": "Why Innocent People Plead Guilty",
									"marks": [
										"key-471-zz3ja",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-473-u8kxx",
									"text": " by Jed S. Rakoff",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-474-jjiap",
									"text": "The criminal justice system in the United States today bears little relationship to what the Founding Fathers contemplated, what the movies and television portray, or what the average American believes.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-471-zz3ja",
									"href": "http://www.nybooks.com/articles/archives/2014/nov/20/why-innocent-people-plead-guilty/?insrc=hpss"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-480-7eaq7",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-477-i5kwk",
									"text": "Roberto Saviano: My life under armed guard",
									"marks": [
										"key-476-4gh0z",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-478-ozlbe",
									"text": " by ROBERTO SAVIANO",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-479-8cpmr",
									"text": "As a young writer growing up in Caserta, a suburb of Naples, I felt myself getting more and more angry. There was a war going on between two mafia clans for control of the territory, and violence between them spilled into the streets.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-476-4gh0z",
									"href": "http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jan/14/-sp-roberto-saviano-my-life-under-armed-guard-gomorrah?CMP=twt_gu"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-484-p3vgq",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-482-ltcq4",
									"text": "'Inverted Jenny' Stamp On Auction Block",
									"marks": [
										"key-481-dklqo",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-483-mr2lq",
									"text": "In 1918, stamp collector William Robey bought a sheet of 100 stamps for $24 at a Washington D.C., post office. The sheet featured what turned out to be a very valuable mistake. He sold the \"Inverted Jenny\" — named for the upside-down biplane — stamps for $15,000.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-481-dklqo",
									"href": "http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=96228893"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-489-m15y7",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-486-zbixs",
									"text": "Open access: six myths to put to rest",
									"marks": [
										"key-485-k3l8e",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-487-a5lx9",
									"text": " by Peter Suber",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-488-vegqx",
									"text": "Open access to academic research has never been a hotter topic. But it's still held back by myths and misunderstandings repeated by people who should know better. The good news is that open access has been successful enough to attract comment from beyond its circle of pioneers and experts.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-485-k3l8e",
									"href": "http://www.theguardian.com/higher-education-network/blog/2013/oct/21/open-access-myths-peter-suber-harvard?CMP=twt_gu"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-494-aako9",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-491-6dfur",
									"text": "Tony Judt’s ‘When the Facts Change’",
									"marks": [
										"key-490-bd2hk",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-492-kn019",
									"text": " by SAMUEL MOYN",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-493-8hvz8",
									"text": "“The arc is down,” is how Jennifer Homans, the widow of Tony Judt and an eminent dance critic and historian, describes the age of cruel disappointment that followed the end of the Cold War.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-490-bd2hk",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/18/books/review/tony-judts-when-the-facts-change.html?_r=0"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-499-1kmse",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-496-j38r5",
									"text": "The Fire on the 57 Bus in Oakland",
									"marks": [
										"key-495-6cgwm",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-497-daugx",
									"text": " by DASHKA SLATER",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-498-wz4an",
									"text": "It was close to 5 o’clock on the afternoon of Nov. 4, 2013, and Sasha Fleischman was riding the 57 bus home from school. An 18-year-old senior at a small private high school, Sasha wore a T-shirt, a black fleece jacket, a gray newsboy cap and a gauzy white skirt.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-495-6cgwm",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/01/magazine/the-fire-on-the-57-bus-in-oakland.html?_r=0"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-504-hxgce",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-501-mst0i",
									"text": "What happened when I confronted my cruellest troll",
									"marks": [
										"key-500-1ztf5",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-502-fi02z",
									"text": " by Lindy West",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-503-icun1",
									"text": "For the past three years or so, at least one stranger has sought me out pretty much every day to call me a fat bitch (or some pithy variation thereof). I’m a writer and a woman and a feminist, and I write about big, fat, bitchy things that make people uncomfortable.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-500-1ztf5",
									"href": "http://www.theguardian.com/society/2015/feb/02/what-happened-confronted-cruellest-troll-lindy-west?CMP=share_btn_tw"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-509-8cayy",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-506-gims3",
									"text": "How One Stupid Tweet Blew Up Justine Sacco’s Life",
									"marks": [
										"key-505-i9xnt",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-507-3j5m9",
									"text": " by Jon Ronson",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-508-6004l",
									"text": "As she made the long journey from New York to South Africa, to visit family during the holidays in 2013, Justine Sacco, 30 years old and the senior director of corporate communications at IAC, began tweeting acerbic little jokes about the indignities of travel.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-505-i9xnt",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/15/magazine/how-one-stupid-tweet-ruined-justine-saccos-life.html?_r=1"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-513-sram4",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-511-1o87f",
									"text": "A City of Two Tales",
									"marks": [
										"key-510-7uh04",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-512-8bnqm",
									"text": "Cleveland is becoming a city defined by its collective impatience. Nearly three months have passed since a white Cleveland police officer shot and killed Tamir Rice, a 12-year-old black boy wielding an air gun in a city park.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-510-7uh04",
									"href": "http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2015/02/tamir-rice-cleveland-police-115401_full.html#.VOs0MUIisRk"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-518-22qsy",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-515-cmu9f",
									"text": "The Pigeon King and the Ponzi Scheme That Shook Canada",
									"marks": [
										"key-514-ax20a",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-516-vu0ry",
									"text": " by JON MOOALLEM",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-517-kpeie",
									"text": "The Pigeon King delivered his closing statement to the jury dressed in his only suit. His name was Arlan Galbraith, and he was representing himself.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-514-ax20a",
									"href": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/05/magazine/the-pigeon-king-and-the-ponzi-scheme-that-shook-canada.html?partner=socialflow&smid=tw-nytmag&_r=0"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-523-7dql4",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-520-a7egx",
									"text": "Religion for Atheists by Alain de Botton - review",
									"marks": [
										"key-519-71iba",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-521-9zhfi",
									"text": " by Lawrence Wright",
									"marks": [
										"strong",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-522-y25ni",
									"text": "The novels of Graham Greene are full of reluctant Christians, men and women who would like to be rid of God but find themselves stuck with him like some lethal addiction.",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-519-71iba",
									"href": "http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2012/jan/12/religion-for-atheists-de-botton-review?CMP=twt_gu"
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "posts:best-of-what-i-read-in",
				"slug": "best-of-what-i-read-in",
				"status": "draft",
				"data": {
					"title": "Best of What I Read in [ ]",
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-8-xf9yh",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-cllgl",
									"text": "I read a lot. When I'm on the bus, when I'm traveling, when I'm hanging out with a sleeping baby, when I've got a few minutes spare, whenever. I still read print books, but because I do a lot of my reading in low-light situations, lately I've been reading more and more in my iPad.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-2-dbba4",
									"text": "For that, I've been using a combination of feedly (as my rss feed reader), Pocket (as my collector of longer pieces), and iBooks (for eBooks) and Adobe Reader (for PDFs) to read. I've realized that I read a lot of stuff from around the web--mostly long form journalism--and want to have a place where I keep track of it and share it out both for others and for myself.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-3-zflms",
									"text": "So I'm going to try something new here. Near the end of each month, I'll post a list of the best things I read during that month.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-4-k9byi",
									"text": "Here's that first list, a collection of the best articles (mostly longform) I read in the past month:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-6-0kuzw",
									"text": "“The Jungle Is Obscene” — Werner Herzog’s Visceral Nature Writing",
									"marks": [
										"key-5-kxcjl",
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-7-sijul",
									"text": " ",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-5-kxcjl",
									"href": "http://biblioklept.org/2009/05/15/the-jungle-is-obscene-werner-herzogs-visceral-nature-writing/",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-13-watfz",
							"style": "blockquote",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-9-pbmuo",
									"text": "This was a fantastic collection of diary entries by German film director Werner Herzog, excerpted from his 2010 book "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-11-9fwdd",
									"text": "Conquest of the Useless: Reflections from the Making of Fitzcarraldo",
									"marks": [
										"key-10-d6oo9",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-12-vtuo4",
									"text": "."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-10-d6oo9",
									"href": "http://www.amazon.com/Conquest-Useless-Reflections-Making-Fitzcarraldo/dp/0061575542",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-18-sjhtd",
