						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-190-6quaz",
							"style": "blockquote",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-189-app5c",
									"text": "Here are two statements about NCAA men’s basketball, both true. First, NCAA men’s basketball is manic, unpredictable, full of joyful chaos; it’s a crazy sideshow fans love for its combination of upsets, buzzer-beaters, frenzied comebacks, court-storming, dancing, and weeping."
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "posts:cesare-pavese",
				"slug": "cesare-pavese",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "Cesare Pavese",
					"featured_image": {
						"provider": "external",
						"id": "",
						"src": "https://steelwagstaff.info/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/fotosegnaletiche.jpg"
					},
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-8-gz07a",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-0x2xz",
									"text": "I just finished Geoffrey Brock's translation of Cesare Pavese's poetry: "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-3-46axl",
									"text": "Disaffection: Complete Poems 1930-1950",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-2-e5xe7"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-4-ngoua",
									"text": ". It was outstanding. I think I had been vaguely aware of Pavese as a 20th century giant of Italian literature, but I had never read anything by or about him, apart from some long forgotten praise by Phil Levine, who was my favorite poet as a teenager. It was, strangely enough, in the poet Robert Bringhurst's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-5-czuun",
									"text": "The Elements of Typographic Style",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-6-b3o5y",
									"text": ", a guide to print typography and book composition, that I read this epigraph from Pavese's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-7-zlrmd",
									"text": "Dialogues with Leucò:",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-2-e5xe7",
									"href": "https://www.coppercanyonpress.org/pages/browse/book.asp?bg=%7BA8FECCCA-1BF2-4E83-B0B9-5F1CE8FA145C%7D",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-10-dlbon",
							"style": "blockquote",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-9-41ftp",
									"text": ""
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-12-59ur0",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-11-rp8zn",
									"text": "The quotation struck me with great force. It felt very 'Objectivist,' actually, like something that George Oppen might have written, a cousin in sentiment to these lines from \"Of Being Numerous\":"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-14-ju9nu",
							"style": "blockquote",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-13-b3wbh",
									"text": ""
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-18-l02qd",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-15-tzah1",
									"text": "Intrigued, I did a quick search for more information on Pavese and learned that he was a leftist (anti-fascist) writing in the 1930s and 40s, and hugely interested in American literature (Edgar Lee Master's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-16-brfzd",
									"text": "Spoon River Anthology ",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-17-8e3e4",
									"text": "was a large influence on Pavese's early poems). That was enough for me to head to the general UW library catalogue and order everything they had."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-24-f3oij",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-19-czgfv",
									"text": "I read his poetry first. Geoffrey Brock has produced a fine translation of Pavese, published in 2002 by Copper Canyon press. Pavese published his first volume of poetry, "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-20-xdpcs",
									"text": "Work's Tiring",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-21-oonie",
									"text": ", in 1936, and published a second edition under the same title in 1943, dropping some poems from the first edition and adding several new poems. In the final years of his life (he committed suicide in 1950), he returned again to poetry, publishing "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-22-nwqxr",
									"text": "Death Will Come and Have Your Eyes",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-23-xmu8p",
									"text": ", poetry that is still well known and much beloved in Italy."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-25-cluw6",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "7000",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.info/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/pavese_note-471x600.jpg"
							},
							"alt": "Cesare Pavese",
							"alignment": "wide"
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-32-iabm9",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-26-hrxcn",
									"text": "If you were to read just one Pavese poem to get a sense of his style, and concerns, I'd recommend \""
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-28-hyb2r",
									"text": "Passion for Solitude",
									"marks": [
										"key-27-77b09"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-29-x6una",
									"text": ",\" but it'd really be very difficult to go wrong. His poems are filled with lone men ('un uomo solo'), a lot of hard working despair, a lot of sad women, many prostitutes, a deep longing for 'the hills' and distrust of the industrial city [Turin] where one makes a living. His poem \"Summer (II)\" closes with this phrase that seems emblematic of his style and concerns: \"un duro inumano silenzio\" ("
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-30-z15py",
									"text": "a hard, inhuman silence",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-31-m6jyd",
									"text": "). If we were to look for an echo in American literature, maybe something that might come out of Jeffers, perhaps?"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-27-77b09",
									"href": "http://www.poetryfoundation.org/poem/180248",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-37-oszxa",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-33-ikchv",
									"text": "If you want more than just a little taste, I've been publishing some of the original Italian with my rough translations on "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-35-2kffl",
									"text": "my tumblr",
									"marks": [
										"key-34-zcu04"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-36-fxmle",
									"text": ", and here's a larger, longer collection of some of my favorite passages from Brock's translation."
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-34-zcu04",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.tumblr.com",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-41-ugbjv",
							"style": "h2",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-38-vycv4",
									"text": "from "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-39-kwkq0",
									"text": "Work's Tiring",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-40-zbla8",
									"text": " (1936)"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-43-mfb4d",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-42-80nlr",
									"text": "from “South Seas”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-57-dqkjp",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-44-ctw6d",
									"text": "And since the last time\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-45-ig68w",
									"text": "I went down to swim in dangerous waters\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-46-73rvu",
									"text": "and followed a playmate up into a tree,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-47-zfhdo",
									"text": "splitting its beautiful branches, and since\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-48-qv252",
									"text": "I bashed the head of a rival and got punched—\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-49-c6xlm",
									"text": "so much life has gone by. Other days, other games,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-50-lojbt",
									"text": "other spillings of blood in conflicts with rivals\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-51-d4ph3",
									"text": "of a more elusive kind: thoughts and dreams.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-52-g5gio",
									"text": "The city taught me an infinite number of fears:\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-53-2vvha",
									"text": "a crowd or street could make me afraid,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-54-m9v5p",
									"text": "or sometimes a thought, glimpsed on a face.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-55-pn6do",
									"text": "I still see the light from the thousands of streetlamps\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-56-20ypv",
									"text": "that mocked the great shuffling beneath them."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-59-inohc",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-58-brqmf",
									"text": "From “Ancestors”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-68-usu3r",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-60-4j4q1",
									"text": "Finding companions, I found my own land—\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-61-o34tb",
									"text": "a hard-hearted land, where it’s a privilege\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-62-8vmm5",
									"text": "to do nothing and think of the future.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-63-o869i",
									"text": "Because work alone isn’t enough for me and mine;\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-64-7w8ut",
									"text": "we know how to break our backs, but the great dream\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-65-8okem",
									"text": "of my fathers was to be good at doing nothing.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-66-xxhf2",
									"text": "We are all of us born to wander these hills,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-67-kepvm",
									"text": "without women, clasping our hands at our backs."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-70-quuga",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-69-b4dgf",
									"text": "from “Landholders”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-76-srhps",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-71-ff6mg",
									"text": "The hospital has a garden that smells of earth mixed\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-72-zbxku",
									"text": "with hard work—it’s good air for the sick.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-73-3s7m7",
									"text": "My priest knows the plants and the bushes\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-74-9a85h",
									"text": "better than even his dead, whose faces change,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-75-gpmv9",
									"text": "while the plants and the bushes are always the same."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-78-6z1bp",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-77-5c3l4",
									"text": "from “Landscape (III)”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-88-t2tbz",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-79-224yl",
									"text": "At night the fields and countryside melt\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-80-mw0wf",
									"text": "into heavy shadow; vineyards and trees\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-81-9y8w8",
									"text": "are swallowed—only a hand can know fruit.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-82-8xu67",
									"text": "In this dark, the rag man could pass for a peasant,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-83-mk0aw",
									"text": "except that he steals and even the dogs don’t hear him.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-84-ar33d",
									"text": "At night the land no longer has owners,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-85-dtkb7",
									"text": "except for inhuman voices. Sweat doesn’t count.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-86-pyf4l",
									"text": "In this dark, the plants have their own cold sweat,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-87-cjb8z",
									"text": "and the fields are one field, and each man’s, and none’s."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-90-u6n5o",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-89-ealf6",
									"text": "from “Grappa in September”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-97-pp674",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-91-83egu",
									"text": "The moment has come when everything stops\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-92-g69u6",
									"text": "to ripen. The trees in the distance are quiet,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-93-wevfd",
									"text": "growing darker and darker, concealing fruit\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-94-n00ak",
									"text": "that would fall at a touch. The scattered clouds\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-95-ozwee",
									"text": "are pulpy and ripe. On the distant boulevards,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-96-xgrqn",
									"text": "houses are ripening beneath the mild sky. …"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-100-rnybu",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-98-oggcs",
									"text": "This is the time when each person should pause\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-99-99521",
									"text": "in the street to see how everything ripens."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-102-rtx1h",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-101-rh6ts",
									"text": "from “Ancient Civilization”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-110-vlrji",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-103-wrfgz",
									"text": "People with bodies should let them be seen. The boy\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-104-3vqbw",
									"text": "isn’t sure that everyone has one. The craggy old man\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-105-af1k5",
									"text": "who passed this morning can’t have a body\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-106-cw4cf",
									"text": "as pale and sad as his face, couldn’t have anything\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-107-tdpe1",
									"text": "as frightening as that. No adults, not even\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-108-tt2pe",
									"text": "a young wife giving her breast to her baby,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-109-s95ud",
									"text": "are really naked. Only children have bodies."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-112-bb5a4",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-111-cz175",
									"text": "from “Nocturnal Pleasures”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-125-fmype",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-113-7n93s",
									"text": "It washes us clean, this wind, it reaches the ends\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-114-j1p8h",
									"text": "of streets that open on darkness; the lights\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-115-ac2g2",
									"text": "that shimmer and the nostrils that flare\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-116-9a55j",
									"text": "are struggling, naked. Each odor’s a memory.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-117-m164b",
									"text": "It came a long way, through darkness, this wind\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-118-ki0pn",
									"text": "that dies in the city: down hills and through fields\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-119-dskzc",
									"text": "where the grasses are warmed by the sun\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-120-pc3x4",
									"text": "and the earth is blackened by humors. Our memory\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-121-oggiv",
									"text": "is a sour scent, barely a trace of sweetness\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-122-10zjh",
									"text": "in the deep breath exhaled from the gutted earth\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-123-65hau",
									"text": "in winter. Each odor fades in the darkness;\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-124-t93sr",
									"text": "nothing reaches us here in the city but wind."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-127-q10ih",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-126-sjdln",
									"text": "from “Landscape (V)”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-135-tx59q",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-128-uj4o5",
									"text": "The unfeeling hills that fill up the sky\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-129-e69g9",
									"text": "come alive at dawn, then hold still, it seems,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-130-n89uf",
									"text": "for centuries, as the sun watches them.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-131-tgjnn",
									"text": "Such a joy it would be to wrap them in green again,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-132-zuouq",
									"text": "and to scatter the green with houses and fruit.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-133-68kmo",
									"text": "Each plant would be a miraculous life\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-134-vfn4k",
									"text": "at dawn, and the clouds would make sense. …"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-143-kgw4w",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-136-gok5j",
									"text": "Do these slopes, slapped up in front of the sky\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-137-ppumc",
									"text": "like city buildings, make sense? They’re naked.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-138-2vgez",
									"text": "A peasant up there, stark against the sky’s void,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-139-5zr5a",
									"text": "is absurd, as if her were taking a walk on a rooftop\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-140-h2daa",
									"text": "in the city. It brings to mind a sterile colossus\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-141-xw6vb",
									"text": "of clustered houses: they get rained on, they dry\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-142-it71h",
									"text": "in the sun, and not one blade of grass grows."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-151-r0dz3",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-144-ng643",
									"text": "To cover the houses and the rocks with green—\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-145-1m1fa",
									"text": "so the sky would make sense—you’d need\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-146-v3y3c",
									"text": "black roots to sink deep in the darkness. At dawn\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-147-z9nwx",
									"text": "the light would gush into the earth, with force.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-148-9h3gg",
									"text": "Everything’s blood would be more alive: bodies,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-149-cwgyi",
									"text": "too, are made of veins so dark they look black.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-150-1rotw",
									"text": "Then the peasants who walk past would make sense. (109)"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-153-k9o5w",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-152-sfgl0",
									"text": "from “Revolt”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-166-1a3k6",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-154-fr64o",
									"text": "That rag heap also looks dead, propped there\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-155-8if42",
									"text": "in the blistering sun, agains that low wall. To sleep\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-156-x2ej6",
									"text": "on the street, you have to have faith in the world.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-157-rf7cr",
									"text": "There’s a beard in those rags, and the gathering flies\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-158-vnig0",
									"text": "have plenty to do. People move down the street\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-159-9nkax",
									"text": "like flies—the beggar’s just part of the street.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-160-od4fq",
									"text": "His miserable grimaces are hidden by beard;\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-161-jnhef",
									"text": "like grass, it imparts an air of serenity. He’s old\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-162-91vpt",
									"text": "and could die anytime, facedown in blood,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-163-59m05",
									"text": "yet he looks like an inanimate thing, and he lives.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-164-bi5rm",
									"text": "Except for the blood, everything’s part of the street.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-165-n7w27",
									"text": "And stars have seen blood in the street before."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-168-ajzh2",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-167-d23q5",
									"text": "from “Motherhood”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-175-163ev",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-169-d3wl9",
									"text": "It’s strange for the boys, living without this woman,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-170-q143x",
									"text": "who none of them knew, who labored to make them,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-171-3vi2w",
									"text": "erased herself in them. The woman was young,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-172-te6to",
									"text": "she laughed and she talked, but to take part in life\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-173-p1sq2",
									"text": "is a dangerous game. In the end, that’s how\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-174-1kot5",
									"text": "she wound up: staring in silence, undone, at her man."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-177-4ncbf",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-176-86xmk",
									"text": "from “Atavism”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-181-84z2g",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-178-rit72",
									"text": "If the streets belong to us all, we should enjoy them\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-179-f55uz",
									"text": "without distraction, looking around as we walk—\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-180-cl3pw",
									"text": "now in shade, now in sunlight—through the fresh air."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-184-bnj4x",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-182-2jjki",
									"text": "And every street opens wide like a door\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-183-8b103",
									"text": "that nobody enters."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-188-0c91t",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-185-cl1sh",
									"text": "from “Landscape (VI)” (the last poem in "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-186-lgv01",
									"text": "Work’s Tiring",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-187-09uvr",
									"text": ")"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-197-yoyqf",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-189-4hhn9",
									"text": "The streets, the pure lines of the houses,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-190-oz3jr",
									"text": "retain, in this fog, an ancient tremor:\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-191-dke3n",
									"text": "you can’t, once you feel it, give up on yourself. You can’t\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-192-yg72u",
									"text": "give up the gentle intoxication that comes\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-193-j8d1v",
									"text": "from the things of a pregnant life, things discovered\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-194-12r0j",
									"text": "as you meet a house, or a tree, or a startling thought.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-195-aaogz",
									"text": "Even the big horses, who will have passed,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-196-9l8xo",
									"text": "at dawn, through the fog, will speak of it."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-204-sc11x",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-198-f85s1",
									"text": "Or maybe a runaway boy will return\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-199-ss4es",
									"text": "this very day to this home, as the fog rises\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-200-et9eu",
									"text": "to cover the river. Maybe he’ll forget his whole life,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-201-6zu2m",
									"text": "the hard times, the hunger, the betrayals of trust,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-202-y4cj8",
									"text": "as he stops on a corner, to drink in the morning.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-203-kfs56",
									"text": "It’s worth going home—maybe everything’s different."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-208-bwxnn",
							"style": "h2",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-205-pacpv",
									"text": "from "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-206-ef44m",
									"text": "Work’s Tiring ",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-207-hjw36",
									"text": "(1943)"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-210-k1a82",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-209-44gqg",
									"text": "from “Morning”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-214-02ed7",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-211-v3hru",
									"text": "Each day is a miracle outside of time,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-212-o4reo",
									"text": "beneath the hot sun: a salt light and the taste\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-213-4yequ",
									"text": "of what lives in the sea suffuse the day. (169)"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-216-qjxua",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-215-ga4rm",
									"text": "from “Summer (I)”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-221-89eny",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-217-dydxa",
									"text": "You move your head\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-218-76ixv",
									"text": "as if miracles of air were swirling around you,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-219-1upms",
									"text": "but the miracle’s you. Your eyes and the heat\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-220-fxcri",
									"text": "of memory: they taste just the same."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-223-2w1sd",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-222-9ik8c",
									"text": "from “A Memory”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-232-20d0n",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-224-k2bu0",
									"text": "Nor do the days collect\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-225-vjtjc",
									"text": "on her face or diminish the easy smile\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-226-gbana",
									"text": "she shines on the world. All that she does\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-227-rezpd",
									"text": "is done firmly, and every time seems like the first;\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-228-ig9h0",
									"text": "she’s alive to the end of each moment. Her gaze\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-229-6xkna",
									"text": "is gathered, her body is firm, they unfold\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-230-735fv",
									"text": "in a voice that’s soft, a bit hoarse: the voice\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-231-cddza",
									"text": "of a tired man. And she is untouched by tiredness."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-235-46o5l",
							"style": "h2",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-233-uo1ji",
									"text": "from "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-234-1bcnz",
									"text": "Poems of Disaffection",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-237-mohw8",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-236-3qlxd",
									"text": "from “Song”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-243-6e5fh",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-238-4pwra",
									"text": "Trees too bring together the sky and the earth. …\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-239-ca6wb",
									"text": "Trees too suffer and die beneath clouds;\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-240-24hqi",
									"text": "man bleeds, and he dies—but he sings his joy\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-241-85idb",
									"text": "between the earth and the sky, sings the great marvel\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-242-cj6gz",
									"text": "of cities and forests."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-245-7lx3o",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-244-h9hsv",
									"text": "from “Sad Wine (I)”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-254-n89cm",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-246-m551k",
									"text": "It was beautiful how he cried as he told it,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-247-nwpsx",
									"text": "the way a drunk cries, his whole body in it,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-248-wphgc",
									"text": "and he hung on my shoulder saying, "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-249-mjdfd",
									"text": "Between us",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-250-qu5d8",
									"text": ",\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-251-vh6oy",
									"text": "always respect",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-252-3o254",
									"text": ", and there I was, shaking with cold,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-253-iah4r",
									"text": "wanting to leave, and helping him walk (247)."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-256-cgxmt",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-255-1qtqg",
									"text": "from “The Boy Who Was in Me”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-264-ur9si",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-257-60bkp",
									"text": "The air was fresh, the alfalfa as plush\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-258-d1u27",
									"text": "as deep velvet, sprinkled with redding gray flowers,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-259-mpl8n",
									"text": "and the clouds and the sky caught fire\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-260-uucjn",
									"text": "in the midst of those stalks. On his back, the boy stared\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-261-5rnie",
									"text": "at the sky he’d so often heard praised at the summerhouse.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-262-ihajk",
									"text": "And the sunset astonished. I liked to half-close my eyes\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-263-qsdf9",
									"text": "and enjoy the embrace of the plants; they held me like water."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-266-5lsex",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-265-7oqyl",
									"text": "from “Imagination’s End”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-275-2k4qs",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-267-vjlei",
									"text": "We have only this single virtue: to begin,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-268-5ap7j",
									"text": "each morning, our life—in the face of the earth,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-269-2pfjd",
									"text": "beneath a hushed sky—awaiting an awakening.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-270-d4p3n",
									"text": "Some are amazed that dawn is such hard work;\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-271-hczst",
									"text": "from making to waking a task is completed.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-272-akvpf",
									"text": "But we live merely to give with a shudder\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-273-e2nfn",
									"text": "to the future work and to wake up the earth once.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-274-wsglv",
									"text": "And sometimes it wakes. Then returns to our silence."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-277-hcp8b",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-276-qztb6",
									"text": "from “Reigning Peace”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-283-lz0sx",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-278-b046q",
									"text": "one day\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-279-zfs47",
									"text": "even the young will grow old, and no one will know\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-280-fag8d",
									"text": "with what gaze strangers will knock against things.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-281-0qth4",
									"text": "But a glance at the world will lay anyone out,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-282-rknhq",
									"text": "and everything wakes in the morning."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-285-ywxyw",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-284-22tc9",
									"text": "from “Poetics”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-292-avtif",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-286-f1cdm",
									"text": "The boy is aware that the tree is alive.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-287-hp8on",
									"text": "If the tender leaves force themselves open,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-288-64018",
									"text": "bursting ruthlessly into the light, the hard bark\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-289-fjbsf",
									"text": "must suffer extremely. And it lives in silence.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-290-cuups",
									"text": "The whole world is covered with plants that suffer\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-291-dke1y",
									"text": "in light, not daring even to breathe."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-299-km8uy",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-293-zkblg",
									"text": "… The houses\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-294-6r2r0",
									"text": "are dazzling, transparent in the bluish vapor,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-295-9509m",
									"text": "and the boy raises his eyes. The distant silence\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-296-1xx8p",
									"text": "that can tighten a person’s breath has flowered\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-297-bhjmp",
									"text": "in the sudden light. These are the boy’s\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-298-6sgtt",
									"text": "ancient trees. And the light is the spell of that time."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-302-21tr6",
							"style": "h2",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-300-hhb21",
									"text": "from "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-301-2n6ab",
									"text": "Earth and Death",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-331-xudmj",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-303-zvfvp",
									"text": "Red earth black earth\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-304-2ozcq",
									"text": "you come from the sea,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-305-q0b4w",
									"text": "from the air green,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-306-h7670",
									"text": "place of ancient words\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-307-ti85p",
									"text": "bloodred weariness\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-308-z588v",
									"text": "and geraniums among stones—\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-309-l8iu9",
									"text": "you bear more than you know\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-310-srhbx",
									"text": "of sea and words and toil,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-311-l2nux",
									"text": "you, rich as a memory,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-312-qb29b",
									"text": "as the barren countryside,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-313-l5bps",
									"text": "you, hard and honeyed\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-314-uqvuk",
									"text": "word, old as the blood\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-315-sft3f",
									"text": "gathered in your eyes;\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-316-w43rp",
									"text": "and young, like a fruit\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-317-tl4mi",
									"text": "that is memory and season—\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-318-t8392",
									"text": "your breath rests\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-319-p1x2a",
									"text": "beneath the August sky,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-320-m06e4",
									"text": "the olives of your gaze\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-321-p3t68",
									"text": "calm the sea, you live\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-322-tqizm",
									"text": "and live again\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-323-y8ug7",
									"text": "as expected, certain\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-324-dsvy6",
									"text": "as the earth, dark\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-325-e55b8",
									"text": "as the earth, grinder\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-326-m7vei",
									"text": "of seasons and dreams\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-327-dzztf",
									"text": "that moonlight reveals\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-328-htxq1",
									"text": "to be ancient, like\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-329-sut5t",
									"text": "the hands of your mother,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-330-7i29n",
									"text": "the hollow of the brazier."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-333-h5ofr",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-332-w92mz",
									"text": "*"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-344-hh4v9",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-334-u5zfv",
									"text": "Your gaze is brine and earth.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-335-6hdnu",
									"text": "One day you dripped\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-336-dpqg0",
									"text": "from the sea. There were\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-337-n9ozg",
									"text": "plants alongside you,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-338-23irj",
									"text": "warm ones, they are\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-339-pvy79",
									"text": "marked by you still.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-340-rk4zx",
									"text": "Agave and oleander.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-341-bwgqj",
									"text": "Your eyes enclose everything.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-342-5grhy",
									"text": "Your veins, your breath\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-343-f75v0",
									"text": "are brine and earth."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-346-1oj9y",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-345-6bvqj",
									"text": "*"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-353-n1nbl",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-347-dc7c0",
									"text": "You are the raspy voice\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-348-lhydu",
									"text": "of the countryside, the cry\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-349-vinmb",
									"text": "of the hidden quail,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-350-gjhbf",
									"text": "the warmth of the stone.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-351-3ai2b",
									"text": "The land is weariness,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-352-tnzk8",
									"text": "the land is sorrow."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-355-ayhrz",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-354-c5t2s",
									"text": "*"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-365-nr7gy",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-356-3gxit",
									"text": "Like rock and grass,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-357-hvwef",
									"text": "like earth, you are closed;\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-358-o4qbe",
									"text": "you churn like the sea.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-359-woeo8",
									"text": "No word can possess you\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-360-7fc9h",
									"text": "or stand in your way.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-361-4jqcx",
									"text": "You gather wounds\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-362-ckhxa",
									"text": "as the earth does\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-363-yi2y3",
									"text": "and make of them life, breath\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-364-777c0",
									"text": "that caresses, silence."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-367-e61jp",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-366-3zy8i",
									"text": "*"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-384-b64tv",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-368-k0kkv",
									"text": "And then we cowards\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-369-4r821",
									"text": "who loved the whispering\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-370-fmu4g",
									"text": "evening, the houses,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-371-dgcsl",
									"text": "the paths by the river,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-372-i3ij9",
									"text": "the dirty red lights\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-373-2cfze",
									"text": "of those places, the sweet\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-374-yzh3o",
									"text": "soundless sorrow—\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-375-nb8m7",
									"text": "we reached our hands out\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-376-fs3vu",
									"text": "toward the living chain\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-377-cmrkg",
									"text": "in silence, but our heart\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-378-o3ege",
									"text": "startled us with blood,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-379-jpt4u",
									"text": "and no more sweetness then,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-380-uvv08",
									"text": "no more losing ourselves\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-381-w4fyy",
									"text": "on the path by the river—\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-382-afn5d",
									"text": "no longer slaves, we knew\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-383-b1sy2",
									"text": "we were alone and alive."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-387-6n324",
							"style": "h2",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-385-ujest",
									"text": "from "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-386-q7c8c",
									"text": "Death will come and will have your eyes",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-389-yggz1",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-388-56f2m",
									"text": "from “I Will Pass through Piazza di Spagna”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-402-p0e5f",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-390-t3hey",
									"text": "That street will open,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-391-279si",
									"text": "the stones will sing,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-392-xez4u",
									"text": "my heart will pound, leaping\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-393-pgkf1",
									"text": "like the water in the fountain—\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-394-xsta6",
									"text": "this will be the voice\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-395-yaqz0",
									"text": "that climbs your stairs.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-396-1bj0h",
									"text": "The windows will know\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-397-f3r3q",
									"text": "the smell of morning air\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-398-5siuv",
									"text": "and stone. A door will open.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-399-djagw",
									"text": "The clamor of streets\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-400-gij5a",
									"text": "will be my heart’s own clamor\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-401-q6j49",
									"text": "in the vanished light."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-404-sry8f",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-403-q8v8v",
									"text": "It will be you—still and clear."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-406-8f12r",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-405-xbn9v",
									"text": "*"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-411-18d7t",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-407-ikxvo",
									"text": "You lived in silence, life\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-408-xwjsd",
									"text": "right before your eyes\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-409-p4cs2",
									"text": "(no pain no fever no shadow)\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-410-ht9ie",
									"text": "like a morning sea, clear."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-418-8s87w",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-412-0l3tu",
									"text": "…Not sorrow not fever then,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-413-h7xyt",
									"text": "not this leaden shadow of day,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-414-mukfq",
									"text": "crowded and different. O light,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-415-t0kao",
									"text": "distant clarity, difficult\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-416-pfl1a",
									"text": "breath, turn again your clear\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-417-uiz4q",
									"text": "and motionless eyes to us."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-420-9dfg0",
							"style": "h3",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-419-leu3g",
									"text": "from “The Cats Will Know”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-423-sh285",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-421-hi50m",
									"text": "There will be other days,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-422-pug5d",
									"text": "there will be other voices."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-428-jnw0f",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-424-zuwxo",
									"text": "… There will be other days,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-425-lvojw",
									"text": "other voices and renewals.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-426-x5nop",
									"text": "Face of springtime,\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-427-3n65m",
									"text": "we will suffer at daybreak."
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "posts:nba-champions-scoring-data-reflections",
				"slug": "nba-champions-scoring-data-reflections",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "NBA Champions and Scoring Data: Further Reflections",
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-5-7zyie",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-ubb77",
									"text": "In the last post, I looked at a few statistical measures to get at just how exceptional the 2014 San Antonio Spurs were in relation to previous NBA champions, particularly in regards to their approach to scoring. By those measures, they had the least 'top-heavy' distribution of points of any NBA champion, and it wasn't really very close.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-2-e8ynu",
									"text": "Another way to look at scoring balance is to examine the raw point differentials between the top scorers on a given team. If I had more time, I could have gathered more data, but I only gathered data on the three leading scorers for each NBA champion. In the first graph, you can see the NBA champions with the smallest variation in point totals between their top three scorers (teams point differential between the leading and third leading scorer was less than 410 points, ~5ppg):\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-3-amrea",
									"text": "There are 25 teams on this list. If we narrow the point differential between 1st and 3rd to 328 points (~4ppg), we're left with the following 15 teams:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-4-3cyp2",
									"text": "Since 1954, the median number of wins for an NBA champion is 57.41. The median number of wins for these teams is 57.08, so they don't seem to be exceptionally good or lucky. Is there anything particularly noteworthy about these 15 teams? Well, yes, I'd say. Here are some interesting observations:"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-7-nwvx1",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-6-u2zim",
									"text": "Only four franchises appear on this list: the Boston Celtics (10x), the San Antonio Spurs (2x), the Detroit Pistons (2x), and the Seattle Supersonics (1x)."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-9-t86rn",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-8-clw53",
									"text": "The Boston Celtics teams from 1957-1963 had exceptional scoring balance among their top three: the only time they don't appear on this list is 1958, when they lost the title to the St. Louis Hawks."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-11-nh5mq",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-10-uk066",
									"text": "Both 'Bad Boys' Pistons champions made the list, as well as the 2005 (Duncan, Parker, Ginobili) and 2014 (Parker, Duncan, Belinelli) flavors of the Spurs, almost a full decade apart."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-14-48t8k",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-12-6uxoe",
									"text": "Suppose, however, that we're less interested in the gap between the top three scorers and only want to know about the team's top two scorers. Here's a similar graph showing the NBA champions with the smallest point variation between the top two scorers (less than 164 points, ~2ppg):\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-13-ttjkv",
									"text": "Some observations about the 13 teams on this list:"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-16-x7h4g",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-15-yes2e",
									"text": "The highest scoring duo on this list are Gail Goodrich (25.9 ppg) and Jerry West (25.8 ppg) from the 1972 Lakers. They're the third highest scoring duo (in terms of raw points) to ever win an NBA title (behind Kareem and Oscar Robertson in 1971, and Michael and Scottie in 1992), and one of just two teammate pairs to average more than 25 points per game on an NBA champion (the other pair to accomplish the feat were Shaq and Kobe, who did it twice: in 2001 and 2002)."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-18-9l39l",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-17-aaqq6",
									"text": "There are 5 Red Auerbach teams (3 that he coached, 2 he was GM of) and 2 Gregg Popovich teams on this list."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-27-ppmd6",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-19-fypk6",
									"text": "This list presents a really interesting mix of teams from different eras. Teams on this list by decade:\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-20-nuj19",
									"text": "1951-1960: 1 (1957 Celtics)\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-21-db3pm",
									"text": "1961-1970: 4 (3 Celtics teams and the 1970 Knicks)\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-22-twist",
									"text": "1971-1980: 3 (1972 Lakers, 1976 Celtics, 1978 Bullets)\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-23-7gvw6",
									"text": "1981-1990: 2 (1982 Lakers, 1990 Pistons)\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-24-jcize",
									"text": "1991-2000: 0\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-25-lvqoj",
									"text": "2001-2010: 2 (2004 Pistons, 2005 Spurs)\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-26-zknbu",
									"text": "2010-present: 1 (2014 Spurs)."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-33-670se",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-28-qeuvv",
									"text": "So these are, by one measure at least, the most balanced teams (in terms of scoring) to win NBA titles (note that the 2014 Spurs appear on both lists, with the sixth smallest variance between their top three scorers, and second smallest variance between their top two scorers).\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-29-2px55",
									"text": "Let's take a look now at the other end: the most offensively "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-30-jouul",
									"text": "imbalanced",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-31-lh8s2",
									"text": " teams, or the teams with the largest variation between their largest scorer and the rest of the team. Here's a graph of the NBA Champions with the largest variation in scoring between their leading and second leading scorers (at least 680 points, ~8.5ppg):\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-32-ni2vv",
									"text": "There are fourteen teams that meet the criteria specified above. Some interesting observations:"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-35-nnuz7",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-34-n1rei",
									"text": "All 6 of Jordan's Bulls championship teams appear on this list."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-37-5sn4p",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-36-60kxe",
									"text": "Rick Barry's 1975 Warriors team comes in second, though would be first if you measure by difference in PPG between the two leading scorers (Scottie Pippen missed more than half the season in 1998, which meant that in terms of raw points, Toni Kukoc was the Bulls' second leading scorer that season)."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-39-t6rp1",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-38-f2f8r",
									"text": "Though we probably most commonly think of the 1980s as the beginning of the NBA's 'star era,' that descriptor is probably best applied to the 1990s: Every NBA champion from 1991 through 2000 appears on this list, except for the 1999 strike-shortened season champions San Antonio Spurs."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-48-q95rd",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-40-2tioj",
									"text": "Teams on this list by decade:\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-41-xzdz3",
									"text": "1950-1960: 0\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-42-6bouk",
									"text": "1961-1970: 1 (1965 Boston Celtics)\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-43-0kc8p",
									"text": "1971-1980: 2 (1971 Bucks and 1975 Warriors)\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-44-eailj",
									"text": "1981-1990: 0\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-45-pdosq",
									"text": "1991-2000: 9\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-46-9t82f",
									"text": "2001-2010: 2 (2006 Heat and 2010 Lakers)\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-47-zmrfg",
									"text": "2011-present: 0."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-51-c84g4",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-49-f74ar",
									"text": "Now let's take a look at the teams with the largest variation between the first and third leading scorers. In this case, we'll use a cutoff of a 1066 point differential between the team's first and third leading scorer (~13 ppg). Here's the corresponding graph:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-50-r1pyj",
									"text": "There are 14 teams that meet this criteria. Some interesting observations about this graph:"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-53-9nx0a",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-52-millp",
									"text": "Jordan (and Pippen)'s Bulls teams again dominate this list, filling the top 5 spots and 6 of the first 9."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-55-13h0i",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-54-bzs22",
									"text": "Shaq and Kobe's 2000-2002 Lakers teams all  made this list, as did Kobe's 2009 team (mostly because Andrew Bynum, the team's third leading scorer by points per game, missed almost half the season)."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-57-q46ua",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-56-akt2n",
									"text": "Olajuwon's two Jordan retirement years teams are here, as are the 1975 Warriors (Rick Barry's one man offense) and the 1971 Bucks (Kareem and Oscar and Bob Dandridge)."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-59-0nqpx",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-58-jqdqa",
									"text": "11 of the 14 teams (all but the 1971 Bucks, the 1975 Warriors, and the 2009 Lakers) won their titles in the 12 seasons between 1991-2002. The only title winner from this era not to make this list? The 1999 Spurs, who played a strike shortened 50 game season."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-61-9y16r",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "number",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-60-dj5vv",
									"text": "If we were to set a the cut-off a little higher, at 1230 points (15ppg), the list would include Jordan (6x), Kobe (3x)/Shaq (2x), and Rick Barry (1x), and that's it."
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "posts:nba-champions-scoring-data-initial-impressions",
				"slug": "nba-champions-scoring-data-initial-impressions",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "NBA Champions &amp; Scoring Data: Some Initial Impressions about the 2014 Spurs",
					"featured_image": {
						"provider": "external",
						"id": "",
						"src": "https://steelwagstaff.info/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/spurs-1.jpg"
					},
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-21-tjasq",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-bsbb2",
									"text": "One of my personal/professional goals for this summer has been to learn how to work with and visualize data. I want to know how to make beautiful data visualizations, and tell interesting stories with the use of data. To that end, I've started working through some self-directed reading, and signed up for a couple of open online courses. The first course I completed was Google's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-3-p8v8m",
									"text": "Making Sense of Data",
									"marks": [
										"key-2-lrmfo"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-4-kqdqj",
									"text": " course. The course itself is pretty sleek and activity driven (it took me part of two days to complete the whole thing), and it seems primarily designed to introduce users to very basic data management concepts and train them to use their experimental "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-6-qsg1u",
									"text": "Google Fusion Tables",
									"marks": [
										"key-5-de7z6"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-7-810om",
									"text": " tool. I've been working on a couple of data projects using the tool. The first has to do with global university rankings (more on that one later), and the second is a fun project that was intended to answer some questions that have been kicking around in my mind since the San Antonio Spurs won the 2013-2014 NBA championship.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-8-knghy",
									"text": "I didn't follow the most recent NBA season very carefully; in fact, I really only saw parts of a couple of playoff games. Even though I don't watch the actual games very often anymore, I still read sports journalism fairly avidly, and have been especially intrigued by the recent explosion of interest in and coverage of advanced analytics (witness the meteoric rise of the "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-10-ikt4h",
									"text": "MIT Sloan Sports conference",
									"marks": [
										"key-9-d05mp"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-11-t6obm",
									"text": " over the past half-decade, for example). I had a range of questions about the Spurs this year, inspired in part by what seemed to me to be an unusually balanced team: for those who don't follow basketball closely, it's worth noting that Gregg Popovich has gained notoriety in recent years for (among other things) "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-13-fqb9y",
									"text": "judiciously regulating his aging stars' regular season minutes",
									"marks": [
										"key-12-eszkb"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-14-0qepe",
									"text": ", and for developing "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-16-9amih",
									"text": "a deep cast of role players",
									"marks": [
										"key-15-zhp4r"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-17-j59ic",
									"text": " which are deployed in novel and ultimately successful ways.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-18-jkxxv",
									"text": "Despite the lack of (or perhaps because of) a single offensive focal point, the Spurs seemed like (from what I saw of them) an absolute offensive juggernaut: one of the few parts of the playoffs I saw was the first half of Game 3 of the Finals, a game in which the Spurs went nearly 11 minutes without missing a field goal, shooting better than 86% in the first quarter and better than 75% in the half. With seven minutes to go in the first half, in fact, they had made 19 of 21 attempted field goals.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-19-s3b7e",
									"text": "It was the most breathtaking display of offensive basketball I have ever seen: fluid, team-oriented, lethal. I couldn't imagine them losing the series, and after they had defeated the Heat in 5 games and Kawhi Leonard was named Finals MVP, I started racking my brain in search of another comparable team. I didn't come up with anything, and started wondering whether systematic statistical analysis, albeit of the fairly rudimentary sort of which I am capable, might bear out my hunch.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-20-dytdf",
									"text": "[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1280\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-2-lrmfo",
									"href": "https://datasense.withgoogle.com/course",
									"blank": true
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-5-de7z6",
									"href": "https://support.google.com/fusiontables/answer/2571232?hl=en",
									"blank": true
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-9-d05mp",
									"href": "http://www.sloansportsconference.com/?page_id=1851",
									"blank": true
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-12-eszkb",
									"href": "http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/early-lead/wp/2012/11/30/gregg-popovich-spurs-await-word-from-david-stern/",
									"blank": true
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-15-zhp4r",
									"href": "http://www.sbnation.com/nba/2014/7/8/5880289/spurs-free-agency-boris-diaw-patty-mills",
									"blank": true
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-22-dsvzv",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://ballislife.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/LeonardMVP.jpg",
								"url": "http://ballislife.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/LeonardMVP.jpg"
							},
							"alt": "Kawhi Leonard and Bill Russell"
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-38-k00wd",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-23-2mu3r",
									"text": "Kawhi Leonard receives the Finals MVP trophy from Bill Russell. Photo: Getty Images.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-24-et9qp",
									"text": "I decided to gather two fairly simple data sets--I went back and looked at every NBA champion (from 1947) and every team with a winning percentage greater than 75% (teams that won at least 62 games in an 82 game season). I recorded a few pieces of information about each team: their regular season win-loss record (and winning percentage), the team's average points per game, their three leading scorers (and their PPG), and the number of players on the team who scored more than 8 points per game while appearing in more than 50 games for the team (I later went back and looked at how many players scored more than 7.5 points per game). I also did several calculations using this data, estimating the percentage of the team's points scored by the leading scorer, the percentage scored by the team's three leading scorers, and the point differential between the top three scorers on each team, for example. For the purposes of this analysis I will exclude the data from all seasons prior to 1954-1955, the first season in which the 24 second shot clock was in use.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-25-86nvy",
									"text": "One of the first features that I found unusual about the 2014 Spurs was that their leading scorer during the regular season, Tony Parker, scored just 16.7 points per game (an average which ranked just 41st in a 30 team league). With the possible exception of the 2004 Detroit Pistons, I couldn't think of an NBA Champion from the recent past with a leading scorer who scored so (relatively) little. A closer look at the data confirmed my suspicion. In the NBA seasons played since 1953-1954, there has never been a league champion whose leading scorer scored fewer points per game than Tony Parker (the Spurs' leading scorer) in 2013-2014. Here's a visualization of the data:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-26-55mx1",
									"text": "If we look at the historical data, we find that the lowest scoring 'lead scorers' for NBA champions (measured by points per game, independent of how many games that scorer played) occurred in 1954 and 1955 (the first two years of the shot clock), 1959-1964 (Boston Celtic teams which featured very balanced scoring, often with 6 or more players scoring in double figures), 1976-1979 (just before Larry Bird and Magic Johnson arrived, this stretch is generally considered one of the low points of NBA history, with the league racked by drug addiction and other problems), the notoriously physical 1989-1990 Detroit Pistons (see the recent "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-28-494c1",
									"text": "Bad Boys",
									"marks": [
										"key-27-53d3v"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-29-hdrud",
									"text": " documentary for a primer), and another famously dull and defensive period in NBA history: 2004-2008 (which featured relatively low scoring lead scorers in every year from this period except for 2006, when Dwyane Wade's Heat won the title with "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-31-adq5a",
									"text": "help from NBA refs",
									"marks": [
										"key-30-8hwst"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-32-dzqt5",
									"text": ").\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-33-9r01j",
									"text": "That's just looking at points per game, not raw scoring totals. Obviously, the average rate of scoring has varied a great deal in NBA history, with post-1954 championship teams scoring anywhere from 90 (the 2004 Detroit Pistons) to 125 points per game (the 1967 Philadelphia 76ers). And points per game is an average based on the number of games each player appeared in, not a raw measure of total points scored. To help account for both of those potential variants, I've also made a graph which shows the percentage of the team's total points scored by their leading scorer (in raw terms, not per game averages). Using this method, the 2014 Spurs appear even more extraordinary:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-34-99utv",
									"text": "If that weren't enough, the 2014 Spurs look even more like an extreme outlier when you perform the same calculations for top the three scorers. Looking at raw point totals, the top three scorers on the 2014 Spurs (Tony Parker, Tim Duncan, and Marco Belinelli) scored less than 37% of the team's total points. The team whose three leading scorers composed the next smallest percentage of the total were the 1977 Portland Trail Blazers, with just under 43%. You can explore the historical data below:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-35-q9txp",
									"text": "As the previous chart indicates, the second notable feature about this most recent Spurs team was their scoring depth. In addition to calculating the percentage of a team's points scored by their 3 leading scorers, I recorded how many players appeared in at least 50 games and scored at least 8 points per game for each NBA champion. That data can be seen below:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-36-c5znr",
									"text": "Again, this chart helps visualize just how unique last year's Spurs were in NBA history. Among all other NBA champions, only the 1966 Celtics had 9 players score more than 8 points per game, and only two other teams in NBA history have even had 8 players hit that benchmark, none since 1977. After the NBA expansion in 1988 and 1989, in fact, only the 1990 Detroit Pistons have even had as many as 6 players score more than 8 points per game in at least 50 games, all of which makes last season's Spurs even more exceptional within their recent historical context.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-37-mo8nz",
									"text": "This post has already run on longer than I initially intended, so I'll leave it for now. More to come soon!"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-27-53d3v",
									"href": "http://espn.go.com/30for30/film?page=badboys",
									"blank": true
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-30-8hwst",
