						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-54-xd8de",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-53-r6f8y",
									"text": "Missy Harris (Caldwell)"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-57-mpy0q",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-55-62lp5",
									"text": "Desiree Heide",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-56-2i3m2",
									"text": " (Payette): Went to BYU-Idaho (then Ricks College) on a journalism scholarship, wrote for the school newspaper. Moved to New York to be a nanny, then moved to Argentina for 18 months as an LDS missionary. Earned bachelor's degree in sociology (emphasis in child and family studies) from BYU-Idaho, completed internships at children's hospitals in St. Louis and Dallas. Worked for three years as a Child Life Specialist at a children's hospital in Austin, TX in 2008. Now works at St. Jude Children's Research Hospital in Memphis, TN, providing psychosocial care to kids with cancer and their families, and help them understand their diagnosis, cope with their experience, have fun if possible, and prepare for their end of life journey if necessary."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-62-z3ds0",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-58-4p8mp",
									"text": "Nancy Henke",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-59-fix8s",
									"text": " (Boise): W"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-60-mike0",
									"text": "ent to Boise State and majored in English and was on the debate team. Worked for the Boise City Housing Authority"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-61-6jcos",
									"text": ", then became Healthcare Services Coordinator at the Muscular Dystrophy Association in Boise. Started grad school at Colorado State University (in Literature) and graduated in 2010. Works at CSU -- teaching composition, literature, doing curriculum development for the first-year composition program, and mentoring graduate students who teach comp. Married a computer geek. Two cats. "
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-65-4pzso",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-63-xh4w0",
									"text": "Matthew Hotham",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-64-rrawo",
									"text": " (Boise): Went to school at Colgate University (double-majored in Creative Writing and Religion), earned MFA in poetry in Syracuse, interned at BOA editions, did two years at Harvard Divinity School. now lives in Carrboro, where's he in the PhD program in Islamic Studies at UNC-Chapel Hill. Writing a dissertation on narratives of the ascension of Muhammad into heaven as told in medieval Persian mystical poems. Works as an editor for the Carolina Quarterly."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-69-rovc6",
							"style": "normal",
							"listItem": "bullet",
							"level": 1,
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-66-e3ef6",
									"text": "Loren Jones",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-67-bqwgz",
									"text": " (Cascade): Served in Marine Corps infantry for almost six years. Came back to Boise State as a returning student, majored in theater (and performed at the Kennedy Theater in DC). Working in Boise, still writing (plays and stories) and "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-68-k386b",
									"text": "pursuing a certification through the National Academy of Sports Medicine in personal training."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-71-dduqb",
