							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-65-a4nn0",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/07/steel-and-laurel-35.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/07/steel-and-laurel-35.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-70-ovvdp",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-66-53lva",
									"text": " Cutting the pocket seams in the suit jacket.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-67-7iq16",
									"text": "I took both suits to be tailored--the alterations took about 3 weeks, and needed to be done twice on one of the suits, but I was really pleased with the fit once all the alterations had been made.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-68-e0a8m",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1196\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-69-8lwrw",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/07/steel-and-laurel-269-e1341602938393.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-71-mo5at",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/07/steel-and-laurel-269-e1341602938393.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/07/steel-and-laurel-269-e1341602938393.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-76-68yim",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-72-67xtz",
									"text": " This picture of me and one of my oldest friends Matt is one of the best images I have of the whole dress ensemble.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-73-mll0h",
									"text": "I wore my own shoes--I can't remember where I got them, but I like them. I planned to polish them myself, but didn't plan things out very well--I got all dressed and ready and then realized that if I were to polish my shoes, it would be wise to change out of my formal wear. Will, Laurel's sister Erin's boyfriend, volunteered to polish them for me, which he did marvelously (he's in the Navy).\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-74-b84pv",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1194\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-75-e567s",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/07/steel-and-laurel-23-e1341602972143.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-77-emvld",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/07/steel-and-laurel-23-e1341604732427.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/07/steel-and-laurel-23-e1341604732427.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-80-tvgd7",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-78-j54b9",
									"text": " My shoes, just before Will began to polish them. Thanks again, Will![/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-79-nmo6p",
									"text": "All told, we spent just under $1500 on wedding clothing, split almost equally between the two of us. I feel like I got the slightly better deal, since I have a full three piece suit that can be worn repeatedly in the years to come, as well as a very nice tuxedo, which, while it probably won't be frequently useful to me, will probably be worn more often in the next several years than Laurel's wedding dress. This was one part of the experience that wasn't super personalized for us--we didn't shop at special boutiques or 'buy local,' nor did we do much to customize our clothing from the way it came 'off the rack.' In both cases, our priority was quality for price--and both of us I think felt pleased with the cost, appearance, and quality of the things we wore to our marriage."
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "posts:choosing-a-photographer-videographer",
				"slug": "choosing-a-photographer-videographer",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "#6: Choosing a Photographer &#038; Videographer",
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-4-oc058",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-pz3d8",
									"text": "In talking to several of our friends about planning weddings, it seems that one of the difficult and most stress-inducing experiences for many couples is choosing their wedding photographer. I suppose this is because wedding photographs are such important mementos, the tangible reminders of the day's events, and wedding albums have certainly been one of the crucial ways in which family lore is stored, transmitted, even generated for many people.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-2-oh486",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1147\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-3-tgszr",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-468.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-5-y3oa1",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-468.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-468.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-18-kxp3v",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-6-6wb6u",
									"text": " Future grandkids, take note. Your g-parents were flammable!!! This shot was our idea, obviously.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-7-4unsh",
									"text": "Photographs:\n",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-8-tafo9",
									"text": "We were especially fortunate to have a super talented professional photographer in our family. Laurel's sister, Jennie, has been taking and making incredible photographic art for more than a decade now. So we knew that Jennie would bring her camera, and that we'd be sure to get some great shots in the days leading up to the wedding (and we did!). We also knew that Jennie was our sister and that we wanted her to be able to attend the wedding and surrounding events as a family member and not a photographer, so we decided that we'd look to hire a professional photographer, at least for the wedding and the reception.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-9-tnsxg",
									"text": "To make a long story short, our first thought was to ask "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-11-u4h8j",
									"text": "Sam or Monika Crowfoot",
									"marks": [
										"key-10-pczxs"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-12-t8gfj",
									"text": ", photographer friends of mine in Madison to shoot the wedding. Sam had photographed Laurel and just before we got engaged and we really liked several of the images from that session, and we knew that they had done weddings and would have given us a super-friends rate, which would have been awesome. Unfortunately, their fourth child's due date was really close to our wedding date, so they weren't really a feasible option for the wedding. We contacted several local options, did some pricing, and then asked Jennie if she'd look into photographers in our area and give us her recommendation. She did, and we met with Sarah Maughan of "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-14-plfuh",
									"text": "SLM Photography",
									"marks": [
										"key-13-hgk1g"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-15-zq2fi",
									"text": ". She fed us (pastries) and showed us some of her recent work, and we talked about our vision for a wedding photographer (simple, candid shots of us and our loved ones--nothing elaborate, nothing too posed or staged, but honest, clear, loving photographs of the two of us and several of the people that we loved). Sarah expressed confidence that she'd be able to shoot our wedding day in the way that we wanted, seemed professional and honest, and quoted us a price that we felt was fair and within our budget (I don't feel comfortable giving the exact price that Sarah charged us, but it was under $2000). We decided to book Sarah as our photographer, and she told us that she'd bring her husband Todd along as her lighting assistant and second photographer (it was the first time that they shot a wedding together, which was lovely). In my opinion, one of Sarah's greatest talents is still-life photography, which meant that we ended up with several stunning images of things that were involved in some important way in our wedding day. It wasn't something we were expecting or had given much thought ahead of time, but were really surprised and pleased with.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-16-hme6c",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1145\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-10-pczxs",
									"href": "http://www.samcrowfoot.com/index2.php"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-13-hgk1g",
									"href": "http://www.slmphotography.net/#/about/"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-17-7x01c",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-17.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-19-g0ey4",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-17.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-17.jpg"
							},
							"alt": "Laurel"
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-33-skma0",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-20-wkrua",
									"text": " Here's one example of what I mean: Laurel's hairclips and bracelet next to our onions.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-21-igts0",
									"text": "Sarah and Todd were really kind and treated us very well, and we ended up with hundreds of "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-23-34lkm",
									"text": "really lovely photographs of the ceremony and the reception",
									"marks": [
										"key-22-o4nsw"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-24-zw1q2",
									"text": " (many of them are scattered throughout these wedding planning series posts, but you can see "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-26-cfipa",
									"text": "all of them here",
									"marks": [
										"key-25-037sv"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-27-w7mde",
									"text": " or read Sarah's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-29-stfa9",
									"text": "blog post about her experience shooting the wedding (with several photos included)",
									"marks": [
										"key-28-1wgre"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-30-79ucq",
									"text": "). SLM photograph owns the copyright on all of these images, and they're very important to us, obviously, so please don't use or repost these images without permission.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-31-39s0x",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1146\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-22-o4nsw",
									"href": "http://www.slmphotography.net/#/featured-weddings-c/"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-25-037sv",
									"href": "https://www.dropbox.com/sh/f66wixblxhwdj3l/czleeyp7DU"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-28-1wgre",
									"href": "http://blog.slmphotography.net/2012/05/laurel-and-steel-madison-wi-wedding-photographer-3/"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-32-jse1u",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-413.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-34-pociq",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-413.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-413.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-46-ekkom",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-35-rxh6o",
									"text": " We're hugging a tree (tree-huggers) in our backyard. This one was my idea. Awesome, huh?[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-36-pgjoh",
									"text": "Video:\n",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-37-4ly0f",
									"text": "Laurel and I also decided that we wanted to videotape the wedding ceremony itself, so I checked out a really fancy "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-39-n2me0",
									"text": "Panasonic AG-HMC150PJ",
									"marks": [
										"key-38-sclkp"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-40-ie35z",
									"text": " with tripod from the "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-42-wcgvg",
									"text": "Digital Media Center",
									"marks": [
										"key-41-rpcm8"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-43-5vd0k",
									"text": ", a fantastic UW-Madison campus resource for anyone working on digital media project. The camera was free and super high quality, and we asked Mike Sherk, one of our more technologically-inclined guests, to set it up and operate it at the wedding. The video recorded wonderfully and looked fantastic, but for some reason we didn't get any audio from Mike's recording (looking back, I really wish we had asked him to test it before the ceremony began). Fortunately for us, my sister Bonnie brought her own small hand-held video camera and had set it up on a tripod on the balcony of Gates of Heaven. Her recording wasn't in HD video, and the sound quality wasn't great, but both the audio and video worked, so we at least have video and audio of our ceremony. I still haven't attempted to clean up Bonnie's audio or merge it with the HD video that Mike shot, but I'm planning to get to it sometime this summer. We didn't pay a thing for the video--which suited us great--I only wish that we had checked to make sure the audio was recording properly on the Panasonic.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-44-9gapj",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1148\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-38-sclkp",
									"href": "http://www.panasonic.com/business/provideo/ag-hmc150pj.asp"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-41-rpcm8",
									"href": "https://dmc.wisc.edu/index.php"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-45-3r18o",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-581.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-47-7bqfy",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-581.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-581.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-51-y37so",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-48-4nb28",
									"text": " We projected a few minutes of Bonnie's film of the wedding ceremony at the reception (the vows and that important bit at the end where Jen pronounces us married).[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-49-ezv9n",
									"text": "The other wonderful surprise from all of this was that my sister Bonnie had her hand-held camcorder because she decided to make a short film for us as a surprise wedding present for us. Unbeknownst to us, she had stealthily recorded nearly all of our friends and family telling stories and sharing memories about Laurel and I at the pizza party the night before, video taped the wedding ceremony, and then got a lot of footage from the reception. About 2 weeks after the wedding, we got a small package from Bonnie with two DVDs in it--she had made a documentary film lasting nearly 2 hours which documented our wedding weekend. We watched the first disc right away--it was wonderful and very touching, and have saved the second disc--we keep planning to watch it and then forgetting about it. Perhaps this evening? In any case, it was a wonderfully loving and creative thing for her to have done, and we couldn't have asked for a better record of what took place on that weekend--it's absolutely something we will treasure for decades to come.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-50-l3y3t",
									"text": "Apart from hiring a reasonably priced, kind professional to photograph you wedding day, our advice for photos and videos is pretty simple: have a really creative sister or two and let them do great work. It's that easy! Jennie and Bonnie! We love you and are so glad that you shared your art, care, and talents with us."
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "posts:planning-meals",
				"slug": "planning-meals",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "#4: Planning Meals",
					"featured_image": {
						"provider": "external",
						"id": "",
						"src": "https://steelwagstaff.info/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/7207494506_c683842e91_b.jpg"
					},
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-4-4ma4s",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-n6gkn",
									"text": "One of the most fun (and most tricky) parts of wedding planning for us was selecting the food that we wanted to serve our guests. Weddings have historically been associated with feasting, and we were traditionally minded in at least this respect: that we wanted to share good food and drink with those we loved. Laurel and I are both vegetarians, though, and neither of us felt comfortable with the idea of causing animals to die in order to celebrate our marriage. We did feel some compunction about having a strictly vegetarian wedding party and reception, especially because we knew that many of our guests, including some of the people we have loved most deeply for the longest time, are not vegetarians, and some might even feel a little nervous and uncomfortable trying to happily enjoy a meal without some of the staple foods they're accustomed to eating. So while we felt solid about our own principles and confident that we'd be able to provide varied, delicious meals without animal flesh, we had a little trepidation about how much our guests would enjoy the meal, and whether some of our guests would leave hungry or a little bewildered.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-2-vi5j3",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1079\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-3-dmd5e",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/7207469674_e9f7c8c055_o.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-5-nqryu",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/7207469674_e9f7c8c055_o.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/7207469674_e9f7c8c055_o.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-15-jnohn",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-6-f4swb",
									"text": " I'm eating a slice of the Greek pizza. As you can see, some guests (like my mother-in-law) missed meat so much that they tried to chew on the flesh of party guests. Fortunately I was wearing a thick sweater. All photos on this post taken by Jennifer Bastian, unless otherwise noted.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-7-etbja",
									"text": "Pizza Party Food",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-8-460lb",
									"text": ":\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-9-7ob7q",
									"text": "For the pizza party the night before the wedding we decided to order pizza from "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-11-baisq",
									"text": "The Roman Candle Pizzaria",
									"marks": [
										"key-10-wabr6"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-12-60mp6",
									"text": ", a local pizza chain. We chose them because we really like their pizza, they deliver, we had a substantial coupon (33% the first $100), and they have several different vegetarian options. We ended up ordering 6 different pizzas: the Veggie Candle (spicy Fireworks sauce, banana peppers, and artichokes); the Animal Lovers (one of my favorite titles, actually: broccoli, spinach, onion, roasted red peppers, & fresh basil); Margherita (mozzarella, sliced tomatoes, fresh basil); the Perstoral (pesto, feta, mozzarella, artichoke hearts, roasted red peppers, kalamata olives, and sliced tomatoes); the Greek (green olives, tomato, spinach, feta, and mozzarella); and the Vegan Destroyer (spicy fireworks sauce, spinach, pine nuts, green olives, red onions, fresh basil, garnished with a thick red pepper puree). We ordered 3 16\" pizzas of each type, which ended up being just a little bit more than we needed to feed our roughly 50 guests (we probably could have easily gotten by with 15 pizzas).\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-13-abjmq",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_833\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-10-wabr6",
									"href": "http://theromancandle.com/"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-14-u71aa",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207494506_c683842e91_b.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-16-n4s5p",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207494506_c683842e91_b.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207494506_c683842e91_b.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-20-jysst",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-17-2t8v1",
									"text": " Some of the pizza on offer [Vegan Destroyer on bottom, Animal Lover's in middle, Pestoral on top].[/caption]We also went to Costco and bought several 2 lb. mixes of organic fresh greens. Initially I was just going to buy one, thinking that our guests wouldn't go wild on salad, but my sister convinced me that we'd need \"at least 5 or 6--people eat a lot of salad\"--so we compromised and I bought 4. Our guests didn't even finish a single box, a slightly sad commentary on the state of health consciousness in Wisconsin, I suppose. We made Sarah eat the rest, since she mistakenly thought people would eat a lot of salad. We also picked up a couple of bottles of salad dressing (Newman's Own I think), which seemed moderately popular, at least in relation to the green leaves we were serving.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-18-hnpwl",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1080\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-19-ebkp8",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/7207487524_d0588f0a4b_b.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-21-aoyi1",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/7207487524_d0588f0a4b_b.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/7207487524_d0588f0a4b_b.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-43-krg4e",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-22-2oxw2",
									"text": " This is the only photographic proof that we have that ANY of our guests even touched the salad. Thanks Erin![/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-23-9ana6",
									"text": "Total cost of pizza and salad: $350\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-24-w1jdw",
									"text": "Pizza Party Drinks:",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-25-5962m",
									"text": "Neither Laurel and I are big drinkers, but we still wanted to provide some options for our guests who had a range of tastes in beverages--from teetotalers (most of my family and college friends are still active Mormons) who love nothing more than cold water (but not too cold, mind you!) to Wisconsonians who consider the idea of an evening meal without beer inhuman and almost barbaric. We decided that we didn't want to provide hard liquor at either the party or the wedding reception, since its effects aren't totally consonant with our values and we didn't want our guests to become drunken or rely on alcohol to produce the emotional effects that we hoped good human companionship and sincere affection would produce. For the non-alcohol drinkers, we had both water and orange juice (I bought a few 2 gallon jugs at Costco), and for those who preferred alcohol, we purchased a half-keg of "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-27-zp24x",
									"text": "Spotted Cow",
									"marks": [
										"key-26-cdahl"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-28-ckk9b",
									"text": ", a popular farmhouse ale made locally by the "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-30-4up2f",
									"text": "New Glarus Brewing Company",
									"marks": [
										"key-29-4cyek"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-31-blbla",
									"text": " from "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-33-81cx0",
									"text": "the Party Port",
									"marks": [
										"key-32-5e84r"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-34-z2ddm",
									"text": ", a liquor store near our home and Laurel bought several bottles of organic red (Cabernet Sauvignon made by "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-36-nj9cf",
									"text": "Zaphy",
									"marks": [
										"key-35-qocgv"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-37-uiwzo",
									"text": ", a label owned by Trapiche, an Argentinian vintner in Mendoza, and "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-39-0ajzt",
									"text": "Santa Julia",
									"marks": [
										"key-38-6am3b"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-40-rkbxw",
									"text": ", also of Argentinian make) and white wine (also Santa Julia, I believe) from Woodman's, a grocery store with an enormous wine selection at a little more than $10/bottle, I think. We ordered the keg for pickup about an hour before the pizza party, took it home after the pizza party, kept it on ice overnight, used it at the reception, and arranged for Party Port to pick up it up on Sunday morning at our reception site. I think we had quite a bit left over from the 1/2 keg we had ordered.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-41-semme",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1092\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-26-cdahl",
									"href": "http://www.newglarusbrewing.com/index.cfm/beers/ourbeers/beer/spotted-cow"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-29-4cyek",
									"href": "http://www.newglarusbrewing.com/index.cfm/general/index"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-32-5e84r",
									"href": "http://www.party-port.com/kegs.htm"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-35-qocgv",
									"href": "http://200.59.205.226/trapiche/english/vinos_zaphy.html"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-38-6am3b",
									"href": "http://www.santajulia.com.ar/wine.php?idvinocat=7&idvino=60"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-42-eh9jm",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-7.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-44-7dy1o",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-7.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-7.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-51-r5odt",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-45-zpuim",
									"text": " The keg outside our back door on the morning of the wedding. We live in a safe neighboorhood, thankfully. Photograph by Sarah Maughan of SLM Photography.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-46-0phf7",
									"text": "Total cost of drinks: a little less than $200 for beer (keg plus ice, tap, tub, pick up cost) which was also used the following evening; ~$500 for wine? (I think we bought 40 bottles to use for both evenings, but I have no idea how much was consumed at the pizza party)\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-47-fzpt1",
									"text": "The Wedding Reception Food:",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-48-bgbdb",
									"text": "Catering the wedding reception was a little bit daunting. We wanted to keep our reception fairly small, but once we had received RSVPs from our immediate family and closest friends, that still meant roughly 100 guests. Feeding 100 people is no small feat, and while we briefly considered preparing the food ourselves (with the help of family), we decided that it would be both difficult in the kitchen space we had, and probably impossible in the time we had available to us between the wedding and reception (a wise choice, in the end, since we would have been both stressed and harried--two things that do not go well with feast meals). As we began looking around at various places in Madison for catering options, we knew that we were leaning towards a buffet style dinner so that our guests could choose what they ate (and how much of it) and that we wanted to offer a healthy, fun, diverse vegetarian meal, with more adventurous (tasty) options for daring eaters, as well as more conventional staples for our guests who were more accustomed to eating meat and don't have as experimental a palette.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-49-sg5al",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1095\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-50-kvkez",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-515.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-52-pllrp",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-515.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/steel-and-laurel-515.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-65-7ns3c",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-53-85bg7",
									"text": " The door to Working Class Catering / Iron Works Cafe. Photograph by Sarah Maughan.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-54-pmuq0",
									"text": "Because we were hosting the reception at the Goodman Center, we met early in the catering investigation process with Dustin Skelley of "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-56-u9dir",
									"text": "Working Class Catering",
									"marks": [
										"key-55-e19yr"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-57-o93vp",
									"text": ", a full service catering company run through the Goodman Center (they share space and some staff with the Iron Works Cafe). Having caterers based just a few feet from our reception room was certainly attractive, and the more we learned about Working Class' mission (it's called 'Working Class Catering' because it's something of a working classroom, integrating local teenagers working through their "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-59-c4184",
									"text": "Teen Education and Employment Network program",
									"marks": [
										"key-58-4xep1"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-60-z2dk5",
									"text": " in all aspects of the cooking and serving process) and food sources (predominantly fresh, local, and organic), the more we were convinced that it was the right fit for the meal we wanted to provide our guests. In our meeting with Dustin and one of their head chefs, we picked out a basic menu, finalized the prices and head counts a few weeks before the event, and enjoyed great food and terrific service on the evening of our reception (Working Class' kitchen was literally next door to the reception room). It was very low stress, and we were quite pleased with the quality and freshness of the food.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-61-jl6ht",
									"text": "Appetizers:",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-62-u1yqg",
									"text": "I'm a sucker for Mediterranean food, so I asked if they'd be able to make crustini with roasted red pepper and chevre (goat cheese) along with a cheese, olive, and roasted red pepper platter. They were, they did, and it was everything I had hoped for. So delicious.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-63-6sp5r",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1091\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
