								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-29-4ntwq",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0023.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0023.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-33-w80qi",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-30-htlpv",
									"text": " One of the gold ingots in the graphite mold.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-31-cddxt",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1045\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-32-x387g",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0029.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-34-rmd51",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0029.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0029.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-42-j7yx5",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-35-0cxei",
									"text": " The two ingots just after they were removed from their molds.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-36-d3uz1",
									"text": "Once we had these ingots (they looked like little gold bullets!), we took them and passed them through a motorized set of wheels which had grooves which allowed us to flatten and lengthen the ingot. After every few passes, we coated the gold in a "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-38-6mb3i",
									"text": "boric acid flux",
									"marks": [
										"key-37-lr2ms"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-39-01zk1",
									"text": " and annealed it (subjected it to intense heat so that the molecular structure would be sufficiently loose that we could mold the shape of the gold without breaking or tearing it).\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-40-46jfo",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1046\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-37-lr2ms",
									"href": "http://etsymetal.blogspot.com/2009/05/intro-to-using-boric-acid-flux.html"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-41-t8ka4",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0030.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-43-k33lq",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0030.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0030.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-47-fjpnn",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-44-tz17m",
									"text": " Laurel reaches into the boric acid flux container as she prepares to anneal the gold.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-45-l6mqx",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1047\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-46-fyda0",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0032.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-48-u92ja",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0032.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0032.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-52-breqe",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-49-pob6w",
									"text": " Laurel anneals the gold during the stretching process.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-50-1l118",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1048\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-51-8qcyt",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0035.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-53-h0nhy",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0035.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0035.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-58-o3ts3",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-54-j6s12",
									"text": " I anneal the gold I'll be using to make Laurel's bands. Note the extended length--the ingot has already be stretched quite a bit.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-55-ugn30",
									"text": "For our rings, Hiroko showed us how to consult with a jewelry guide to determine the desired length and thickness for the ring sizes and width that we had in mind, and we stretched the gold until we reached a point where the strips were close to their desired size. This process took us about 4 hours, and was all the work we did on our first Sunday.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-56-1s30y",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1049\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-57-fjqgb",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0038.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-59-vn8zi",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0038.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0038.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-64-z3urx",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-60-vo8t2",
									"text": " The two ingots after stretching.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-61-v15pc",
									"text": "We came back on the following Sunday (February 12th) to resume where we left off. Once the gold had been sufficiently stretched, we then cut the strips to the desired length. The long strip that you see in the image above became three shorter strips (for Laurel's rings), while we trimmed a little off the end of the shorter strip. Then we took pliers and bent the strips inward until they roughly took the shape of ovals--the most important part of the process was making sure that ends were flush and even.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-62-dwf5y",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1052\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-63-0mt8a",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0043.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-65-xjpsr",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0043.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0043.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-70-89zrl",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-66-4gdct",
									"text": " Laurel uses her might to bend the ring into a roughly circular shape.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-67-iii4j",
									"text": "Once the ends were flush and tight, we soldered the rings closed with gold solder and a soldering torch. This was probably the most interesting part of the whole process. We mounted the rings in a little metal holder (it had pincers kind of like robot fingers!), took a couple of flakes of gold solder from the container where Hiroko stored it with tiny tweezers, and carefully placed it directly on top of the seam that we were trying to seal. Then we held a direct flame on the soldering material, which has a melting point just under that of gold. The soldering material got hotter and hotter until it suddenly turned from a solid into a liquid, pouring into and over the gold band and sealing up the seam.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-68-bkruy",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1055\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-69-en5iw",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0046.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-71-2smoc",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0046.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0046.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-75-nbmr9",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-72-zma9x",
									"text": " Laurel prepares to solder my ring.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-73-yopfv",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1056\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-74-wxu8j",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0049.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-76-ryup9",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0049.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0049.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-81-qkzml",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-77-l5ptt",
									"text": " I hold the soldering torch to one of Laurel's rings.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-78-wq9uu",
									"text": "Once it dried we had closed rings (though their shapes were still pretty irregular).\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-79-qtacq",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1053\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-80-pepi1",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0044.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-82-lpws9",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0044.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0044.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-87-3l33e",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-83-geqsd",
									"text": " Laurel's three rings, after soldering but before we made their shapes pretty.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-84-24j3n",
									"text": "The next step involved shaping the rings. To shape them, we took the rough ovals and placed them onto a long metal dowel. Then we took a wooden mallet and tapped the rings, rotating the dowel as needed, until the rings formed more regular circles, there was no space between the gold and the dowel, and the ring had stretched to the target size (ring sizes were marked on the side of the dowel).\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-85-xtoi8",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1057\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-86-abh8c",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0050.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-88-lm1b1",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0050.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0050.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-93-qxze8",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-89-vntss",
									"text": " I'm shaping one of Laurel's rings on the dowel.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-90-qii5d",
									"text": "Once we had hammered the rings to their desired sizes, we took them off the dowel and tried them on to make sure that they fit properly. Laurel's rings were actually a little too snug, so we had to cut, resolder, and resize them. Thankfully we had Hiroko there to guide us through it all, or else I would have been in a lot of trouble. All told, we spent a little more than 3 hours there on the second work day.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-91-w7hu0",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1058\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-92-q0x7p",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0051.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-94-hnwfe",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0051.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0051.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-99-my8a2",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-95-owsza",
									"text": " The rings fit![/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-96-pzcbe",
									"text": "We came back on the following Sunday (February 19th) to finish the rings. We started by sanding the rings on large sheets of sandpaper, rubbing them until the edges were smooth and fairly even.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-97-up97y",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1060\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-98-sqjd5",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0276.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-100-j6di4",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0276.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0276.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-104-bny2k",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-101-nn7ex",
									"text": " Sanding the rings to smooth the edges.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-102-vghe6",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1061\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-103-2aai6",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0278.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-105-z7zfe",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0278.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0278.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-110-hqx44",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-106-yftrr",
									"text": " Proudly holding our sanded rings. That's our teacher, Hiroko Yamada, standing behind us.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-107-c00ey",
									"text": "Once the rings were flat, we then took files and shaped the edges so that they had a slight curve on the outside and inside edge.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-108-9yyga",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1062\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-109-rcscu",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0281.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-111-n7osd",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0281.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0281.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-115-u742t",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-112-u0adh",
									"text": " Laurel files the outside of my ring.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-113-mbhc2",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1063\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-114-y82ea",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0283.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-116-j0b8t",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0283.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0283.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-120-yc20d",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-117-xa0xx",
									"text": " Laurel files my ring.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-118-6l0fi",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1064\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-119-v307p",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0285.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-121-8f5v5",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0285.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0285.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-126-v4lks",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-122-zl8du",
									"text": " Learning to file with the magnifying visor.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-123-gfwqy",
									"text": "It took me quite a while to really get the hang of using the file to shape the ring's edges, and even longer to figure out how to use the magnifying visor I was wearing, but it ended up being one of my favorite parts of the whole experience because I could actually see the change in shape and curve that I was making with the file and I began to feel how changes in weight and pressure from my hand would manifest themselves in the gold that I was working with. It's easy to understand how metalworkers can get lost in their art, it's a very sensuous and rewarding embodied experience.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-124-y0k2n",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1065\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-125-r0atw",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0291.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-127-yom2b",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0291.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0291.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-131-q71qh",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-128-7gr52",
									"text": " Two of Laurel's rings, after filing.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-129-qmziv",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1066\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-130-24aj0",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0292.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-132-3x6j3",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0292.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0292.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-137-wh8x9",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-133-mo2mh",
									"text": " Another view of two filed rings.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-134-43h3h",
									"text": "Once the rings were filed and shaped, all they needed was a bit of polish to make them shine. Hiroko did this part for us (it involved a rapidly spinning brush and required a steady but delicate touch).\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-135-m8y5l",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1067\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-136-st36l",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0296.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-138-n3qtp",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0296.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0296.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-142-evqaq",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-139-jo8p7",
									"text": " Hiroko polishes one of our rings while I look on intently.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-140-sv80f",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1068\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-141-ihpxg",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0295.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-143-rcw7a",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0295.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0295.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-147-bpz1v",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-144-bofs5",
									"text": " I'm holding the polished ring that Laurel made for me![/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-145-1ietu",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1070\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-146-1snkd",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0301.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-148-pyngs",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0301.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0301.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-156-jhk1l",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-149-pi0sk",
									"text": " The finished ring Laurel made for me.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-150-n3yj8",
									"text": "Laurel also decided that she'd like a stone set in the center band, and picked out a setting that looked good and a modest gem-cut "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-152-levs0",
									"text": "Moissanite",
									"marks": [
										"key-151-uk9o9"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-153-jv20r",
									"text": " (synthetic diamond) stone that Hiroko placed in a setting for us.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-154-mke51",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1069\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-151-uk9o9",
									"href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moissanite"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-155-nydr2",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0299.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-157-yutjd",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0299.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0299.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-162-pibcn",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-158-ao3zi",
									"text": " Laurel models the center band and setting before the stone is added.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-159-3gvs5",
									"text": "Hiroko finished setting the stone in practically no time, and the rings were completely finished within three hours on our last day in the shop. We almost couldn't believe how beautifully the rings turned out, and were surprised and amazed to see the work of our own hands (we obviously had a master teacher). We went to Noodles for a celebratory meal (Indonesian Peanut Saute!) and took this photograph of all four finished rings:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-160-orjf3",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_1071\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-161-kh7r9",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0303.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-163-fk4ie",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0303.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0303.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-166-1cijn",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-164-l93kf",
									"text": " Finished rings in a jewelry box.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-165-5ftpt",
									"text": "All told we spent about 10 hours working on the rings, spread out over three working Sundays. We also arranged a work trade with Hiroko, who was extraordinarily generous with her time and expertise, so that we ended up paying much less than we ordinarily would have paid for comparable rings at any jeweler. I don't feel comfortable publishing the total cost of the rings, since I think that's a private matter between us and Hiroko, but I will say that Hiroko was an absolute dream to work with. She was patient, encouraging, and funny, and she let us do just about everything in the shop, even when we made mistakes and were doing things awkwardly (we broke a couple of saw blades and Laurel even sliced her finger at one point). All told, it was one of the best shared experiences Laurel and I have ever had, and so much of it was shaped and conditioned by Hiroko, who made us feel comfortable, empowered, and wholly involved in the processes of design and creation. We can't recommend Hiroko's work or her gallery highly enough. She is one of the best and most generous people we've ever known as well as the most gifted metal worker we've ever seen."
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "posts:designing-and-making-invitations-part-1",
