							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-75-b1gxt",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-65-959gk",
									"text": " Design for Ceremony Invitation, printed from InDesign.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-66-w1b4i",
									"text": "For the wedding invitations themselves, I used Day Roman for the text, and took the decorative designs from two different type faces, "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-68-teufm",
									"text": "Circle Things 2",
									"marks": [
										"key-67-f1x1a"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-69-1pz4c",
									"text": " and "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-71-6t6bh",
									"text": "Italian Mosaic Ornaments",
									"marks": [
										"key-70-pt5dg"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-72-drpr6",
									"text": ". The only one of the designs on this page that I made myself was the four interlocking ring pattern in the center of the invitation (made in Illustrator).\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-73-phjhr",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_964\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-67-f1x1a",
									"href": "http://www.dafont.com/circle-things-2.font"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-70-pt5dg",
									"href": "http://www.dafont.com/italian-mosaic-orna.font"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-74-vqz0r",
									"href": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/rsvp_color2.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-76-dwrxr",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/rsvp_color2.jpg",
								"url": "https://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/rsvp_color2.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-110-0po5f",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-77-oxt91",
									"text": " Design for RSVP cards, printed from InDesign.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-78-hto0o",
									"text": "On the RSVP, the title text was in Mutlu and the rest of the page was in Day Roman. The hearts in the starbursts were taken from a typeface called "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-80-hkexe",
									"text": "Heart Things",
									"marks": [
										"key-79-ysulk"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-81-0ds1u",
									"text": ". I designed the diamond-based patterns at the outside of the top and bottom of the RSVP as well as the divider pattern and interlocking circles in Indesign and took the other shapes on the bottom row from Circle Things 2 and Italian Mosaic Ornaments.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-82-m6bxi",
									"text": "Once I had finished the designs, I sent single color PDFs of the design away to a printing company who makes high quality negative transparencies. It took about 2 weeks to get the negatives back, and then I cut them out of the larger sheet, placed them on a photopolymer sheet, developed the image, washed and baked the plate and then cut out the finished polymer plate and stuck it to a thin adhesive backing so it could be mounted onto the press bed. If that sounds complicated, here's an accurate but slightly corny tutorial video.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-83-buyuo",
									"text": "[youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y8hBGDhC0CE&w=500&h=375]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-84-1ioro",
									"text": "For the paper, I went to "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-86-6ww0x",
									"text": "Artist and Craftsman",
									"marks": [
										"key-85-ox8ba"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-87-5bqkz",
									"text": " (an art supply shop off of State Street in Madison) and bought several 22\"x30\" sheets of "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-89-27bbp",
									"text": "250 gsm Canson printmaking paper",
									"marks": [
										"key-88-y48tc"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-90-uu1n7",
									"text": " in a cream color that we really liked. The invitations were 4.25\"x5.5\" (made to fit inside A2 envelopes) and the RSVP cards were 3.5\"x5\" (made to fit A1 sized envelopes, the smallest permitted by the post office), and I cut the paper by hand on a paper cutter in my letter press classroom (unfortunately, I miscalculated the size for some of the pieces, which caused me to lose the deckled edge that I had hoped would be on the bottom of all of the invites and RSVPs on about a quarter of the total press run. I bought "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-92-n517v",
									"text": "100 square-flap red A2 envelopes",
									"marks": [
										"key-91-gaxh2"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-93-urxub",
									"text": " and "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-95-cfto1",
									"text": "100 square-flap cream A1 envelopes",
									"marks": [
										"key-94-oh51r"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-96-04yr1",
									"text": " online and printed our mailing address on the RSVP envelope and our return address in the top left and website on the flap of the outer envelope.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-97-u1zb9",
									"text": "I made several videos with my iPod documenting various stages of the letter press process, which I've embedded below.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-98-fzfkg",
									"text": "Cutting Paper:\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-99-78789",
									"text": "[vimeo http://www.vimeo.com/43066467 w=500&h=889]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-100-kszar",
									"text": "Printing Reception Invitations:\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-101-q2ffj",
									"text": "[vimeo http://www.vimeo.com/43066470 w=500&h=889]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-102-pf1yo",
									"text": "Printing RSVP Cards:\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-103-wfhqc",
									"text": "[vimeo http://www.vimeo.com/43066468 w=500&h=889]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-104-pquk6",
									"text": "Printing Envelopes:\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-105-b8dgp",
									"text": "[vimeo http://www.vimeo.com/43066471 w=500&h=889]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-106-72tjm",
									"text": "Overall the process was time-consuming and tricky, but lots of fun. I learned a ton from the experience, both things to avoid in the future, and things I'd definitely do again. The biggest surprise for me in the design process was how much smaller the negatives and plates looked in real life as compared to their size on my computer screen. I suppose I should have known that 4\"x6\" wasn't going to be very large, but a lot of the detail that I could see on the digital scale wasn't exactly able to carry over all the way to the polymer plate (there was some blurring and smearing on small details, especially on the tiny diamond shape designs I made at the top of the RSVP card. In the future, I think I'd make my design a little bigger and less complicated--in such a small space I think the designs felt a little too busy and could have been given more white space to breathe in. Other tricky elements in the process were learning to do two-color printing--on a letter press, every color requires a separate run through the press, which makes for all kinds of challenges when it comes to registration and press set-up. When I first started on the invitations, I didn't know anything about mixing ink, and I somewhat stupidly printed the front twice (once in red and once in black) before turning it over and printing the back an additional two times (once in red and once in black). Doing it this way required me to ink and clean the rollers four separate times instead of doing all the black printing (front and back) first, and then cleaning the rollers and doing all of the red printing (front and back). This turned out to be a special problem in my case because the second time I went to ink the rollers in red, the person using the press before me hadn't done a thorough job cleaning off the rollers, which meant that the red color I mixed up was a little big darker than the first red I used. No one said anything about it, but I noticed the difference in color, and would have preferred a consistent shade of red on the front and back of all invitations.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-107-nm31r",
									"text": "Total Cost: less than $100. Having free access to lots of supplies through my art class definitely helped (ink, photopolymer plates, Vandercook presses, etc.), so my primary expenses were for the negatives (around $20) and the paper (at roughly $2.30 for each 22\"x30\" sheet). If you have the time and the interest in design, we found that making the invitations yourself (even if you have them printed conventionally at your local print shop) is a great way to save lots of money. And it's really fun!\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-108-l23g4",
									"text": "Here's how the finished invitations and RSVP cards looked:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-109-04ua4",
									"text": "[gallery type=\"rectangular\" ids=\"929,928,930,927,931,932,934,933,936,937,938,939,940,941,943,942,945,948,952,946,951\"]\n\n"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-79-ysulk",
									"href": "http://www.dafont.com/search.php?q=heart+things"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-85-ox8ba",
									"href": "http://www.artistcraftsman.com/"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-88-y48tc",
									"href": "http://www.danielsmith.com/Item--i-159-920-003"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-91-gaxh2",
									"href": "http://www.desktopsupplies.com/enrea243x53.html"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-94-oh51r",
									"href": "http://www.desktopsupplies.com/cream-a1envelopes-100.html"
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "posts:events-and-venues-part-1",
				"slug": "events-and-venues-part-1",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "#1a: Events and Venues Part 1",
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-15-wjsrc",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-9i141",
									"text": "This is the first in a series of what I hope will be several posts looking at specific aspects of our wedding preparations. In this post I'll describe our decisions around the events of the weekend on which we got married and the venues where we decided to hold those events.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-2-1kwsf",
									"text": "The first and most important event for us to plan was the ceremony itself. In our earliest discussions, Laurel and I agreed that we wanted to have a small, intimate ceremony, with no more than 30-40 guests: immediate family, godparents, and close friends travelling from out of town. This wasn't meant to slight anyone, just to keep the ceremony at a human scale. We both agreed that we wanted to have a secular ceremony, as neither of us are currently active in a particular community of faith, and neither of us identified a local church or place of worship that we wanted to use for the ceremony. Laurel was the advance scout on wedding venues, and gathered information about several prominent sites in and around Dane County, several of which offered package deals for both a ceremony and reception. I think this was the first instance in which I experience sticker shock--I was surprised and a little sickened by the average price for many of the potential wedding sites, many of whom offered one rate for public events and gatherings and another, much higher, rate for weddings. At Madison's beautiful "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-4-pppml",
									"text": "Olbrich Gardens",
									"marks": [
										"key-3-j3dvq"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-5-16iql",
									"text": ", for example, a 3 hour reservation for a wedding ceremony costs either $470 or $750, while the reception room costs $510 or $665, depending on the time slot which it's being reserved for. Olbrich's atrium, the exact space which costs $470 for a three hour wedding reservation, can be reserved for as little as $120 for a four hour block on a weekday, while full-day (from 8 AM - 5 PM) and full-evening (from 5 PM - 11 PM) Saturday reservations "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-7-xtsxa",
									"text": "only cost $325",
									"marks": [
										"key-6-zqy4f"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-8-15s1o",
									"text": ", nearly $150 less than the least expensive 3 hour wedding rental. We found this was fairly typical of wedding venues--the event itself allows venues to charge a premium quite outside of the ordinary market rates.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-9-pbori",
									"text": "Because we planned to have a small wedding and because we wanted to choose a place with special personal significance for both of us, we spoke about the possibility of having the wedding in Fort Atkinson, a nearby community that was important to us because it had been the home of Lorine Niedecker, a favorite poet, and the site of the poetry festival where we had reconnected at the beginning of our courtship ("
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-11-dp3wx",
									"text": "more about that story",
									"marks": [
										"key-10-gueyr"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-12-pif1t",
									"text": ", if you're interested). I contacted Ann Engelman, the president of the Friends of Lorine Niedecker, and asked her whether it would be possible for us to hold our wedding ceremony outdoors at the site of Niedecker's cabin on Blackhawk Island, which is now privately owned. Ann suggested that we write the cabin's current owners to tell them a little about ourselves and our story, which we did, and told us that she'd check in with the owners, which she did. About a week later, Ann emailed to let us know that the owners had given their permission to use the site for a small wedding ceremony and that she'd also checked in with the sheriff's office about parking--and as far as she could see we could proceed with planning our wedding ceremony at the Niedecker cabin. Everyone was pretty excited, especially because as far as anyone knew would be the first time Lorine's cabin would host a wedding. Here's a photo of what the site looks like:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-13-s22uv",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_815\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-3-j3dvq",
									"href": "http://www.olbrich.org"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-6-zqy4f",
									"href": "http://www.olbrich.org/rentals/roomrates_2012.cfm"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-10-gueyr",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/03/winter2012.pdf#page=3"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-14-ct3nm",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0209.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-16-oz4iv",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0209.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0209.jpg"
							},
							"alt": "Photo of Lorine Niedecker Cabin"
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-24-dau1i",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-17-14m2u",
									"text": " Back side of Niedecker Cabin, viewed from near the banks of the Rock River[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-18-jx03i",
									"text": "As you can see, it's not particularly magical, but it was a place of special significance for us, and we thought that it would probably have been pleasant enough by April 21. We would have set up three dozen chairs in a semi circle near the cabin and had our officiant stand up near the three small trees visible just in front of the small shed. The biggest concern we had about using this site as our wedding location had to do with weather--we needed a site that offered some shelter and control of the elements in case it was particularly cold or rainy. Initially we reserved a large shelter in "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-20-ccjzi",
									"text": "Dorothy Cairnes Park",
									"marks": [
										"key-19-nhsxk"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-21-m9g76",
									"text": ", a large (514 acre) conservation park just outside of Fort Atkinson in Jefferson County--which incidentally, is gorgeous and would be a great spot for a wedding as well as being just a beautiful place for a day trip or nature trek (see image below). A few months before the wedding, however, we checked on the availability of the Gates of Heaven building in James Madison Park in Madison and discovered that a two-hour weekend rental for the building would cost just $110.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-22-sunlu",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_819\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-19-nhsxk",
									"href": "http://www.jeffersoncountywi.gov/jc/public/jchome.php?page_id=601&group=Parks&page_name=Dorothy%20Carnes%20Park"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-23-e56lj",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0249.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-25-wssxd",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0249.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0249.jpg"
							},
							"alt": "Photo of Rose Lake in Dorothy Carnes State Park"
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-31-ti9yy",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-26-qq6sv",
									"text": " View of Rose Lake from trail in Dorothy Carnes State Park[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-27-bp10m",
									"text": "Gates of Heaven was available on the morning or April 21st, so we reserved the building from 11 AM - 1 PM. Initially, I was a little concerned about the reservation, because the rental costs also lists what is described as a \"wedding package\"  for $500 (the package includes 2 hours of rehearsal time, 4 hours use of the facility on the day of the wedding and a park attendant for the 4 hours on the day of the wedding). We had no need of the extra features (or the extra costs) of the wedding package, but I was a little nervous about making the reservation, since several venues had previously refused to rent their spaces to me for shorter times and lesser rates once they knew the event was a wedding--many potential venues insisted that I had to rent their wedding package, even if another package seemed  like a better fit for our needs. Because Gates of Heaven was going to be our backup location, I was a little dishonest when they asked me what the reservation was for--I said it was going to be for a \"family gathering\"--which while technically true, also led the woman taking the reservation to believe that we'd be having a family reunion, not a wedding. As it turns out, I needn't have worried--the people I talked to at the City Parks Department Office were very cool, and none of them seemed to mind at all that we were planning to use the building for a wedding ceremony (and not a family reunion) during our 2 hour reservation, and at no point did anyone even attempt to upsell me to the $500 DELUXE WEDDING PACKAGE, for which I was really grateful.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-28-lwp2c",
									"text": "The weekend before the wedding was scheduled, Laurel and I traveled out to Fort Atkinson, where we met our officiant (Jen Gilmour, one of Laurel's oldest friends) who came in from Milwaukee and together the three of us scoped out the location at the Niedecker cabin and tried to visualize what we'd do for the wedding. The weather was a little grey, the ground was a bit soggy, and the current owners of the cabin were doing construction on another building closer to the water, which meant that the site was a little less appealing to the eyes--all reasons for slight concern. We left Fort Atkinson that afternoon a little unsure about the location--on the one hand, it really would have meant a lot to me to marry Laurel at Niedecker's cabin, but on the other hand, it would be more of a headache logistically getting our guests out to a slightly difficulty to find location in Fort Atkinson, where we'd be at the mercy of the weather, which would only add to our stress since it meant that we might be forced to call the wedding at the last minute and change locations. Laurel and I talked it over and slept on the decision, and then decided early in the week leading up to the wedding that as much as we loved the Niedecker cabin and its importance in our own story, it would be easier all around to hold the wedding at Gates of Heaven. We contacted our guests early that week to let them know about the venue change, and went ahead with our back-up plan.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-29-n6qsu",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_826\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-30-ll8xu",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-38.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-32-ywnat",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-38.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-38.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-37-as09k",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-33-pwfxh",
									"text": " The view from our front window on the morning of April 21. Great weather![/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-34-b3y20",
									"text": "As it turned out, the weather on the 21st was gorgeous (despite what had been forecast earlier that week), which meant that an outdoor ceremony at the Niedecker cabin probably would have been lovely, though Gates of Heaven turned out to be such a fantastic location that we didn't regret changing the venue in the least. In terms of cost, beauty, size, ease of rental/use, and location I can't think of any venue in Madison that could possibly be better suited for a small non-denominational wedding. The interior of the building was spacious, full of natural light, simply adorned, and entirely tasteful. The building also features a small balcony at the rear which can hold overflow guests but also lends itself well as a place from which photographs can be taken or video can be filmed.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-35-wu9hr",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_823\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-36-dhovq",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-71.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-38-ogcys",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-71.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-71.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-43-cl5m2",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-39-3ir5o",
									"text": " View from balcony at Gates of Heaven (that's my sister Bonnie setting up a video camera in the left of the frame!)[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-40-uqhwa",
									"text": "There were roughly 25 parking spots behind the building, which was far more than we needed, and the two hour rental gave us more than enough time (especially since no one was using the building before or after us--in fact, I had received a key to the building a few days before the wedding, so I could have even gone to set up chairs the night before after the last event had completed if I had wanted to).  Our ceremony itself took less than 25 minutes from the time that we approached the altar to the time we walked out of the building as a married couple, leaving us with plenty of time for set up before the wedding and lots of hugs, laughter, and photographs after the ceremony.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-41-cuwx6",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_821\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-42-bwlrg",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-1291.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-44-kkdf5",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-1291.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-1291.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-49-27zb3",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-45-tg53n",
									"text": " Gates of Heaven seen from rear when filled with guests (roughly 40 people total)[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-46-mzspl",
									"text": "Besides the ceremony, we also decided to have a pizza party for friends and family the night before the wedding and a reception in the evening after the wedding ceremony. I was planning to write about those in this post, but this has already gone on far too long, so I'll save those for next time.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-47-67ctr",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_822\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-48-r9uq9",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-392.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-50-qeduh",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-392.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-392.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-52-hvvy1",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-51-yzmmp",
									"text": " Gates of Heaven, seen from front after our wedding[/caption]"
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "posts:events-and-venues-part-2",
				"slug": "events-and-venues-part-2",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "#1b: Events and Venues, Part 2",
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-5-uk1ao",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-t5xvm",
									"text": "Yesterday I wrote about our wedding ceremony itself and our decision about where to hold it. Today I want to finish the post by writing about the two other events we held that weekend: a pizza party on Friday evening (the night before the wedding), and our wedding reception held later in the evening on the day our wedding was performed.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-2-4rs6n",
									"text": "The Pizza Party: \n",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-3-v8blh",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_832\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-4-nmxs3",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207491090_95063dbf26_b.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-6-sogzj",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207491090_95063dbf26_b.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207491090_95063dbf26_b.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-14-yj82o",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-7-inu0k",
									"text": " The ceiling of the community center's main gym is lined with flags from the native countries of several of the community's residents.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-8-a86ll",
									"text": "We didn't have a wedding party--no best man or maid of honor, no groomsmen or bridesmaids, and the ceremony itself was brief and fairly simple, so we felt there was no need for a traditional rehearsal dinner. Instead of a rehearsal dinner, we thought it would be fun to have a relaxed, informal party the night before the wedding where we'd eat pizza and salad and let our family and any friends who were in town come and get to know each other a little before the wedding. We reserved the Eagle Heights Community Center (a large gym-like space in a community where I've lived for most of my time here in Madison) because it's walkable from our home, costs just $15/hour and had tons of space and a kitchen facility. While it's a great place to host parties and events like this, it can only be reserved 60 days in advance and I think it's can only be rented by residents of University Apartments which makes it a little tricky for people planning something similar in advance of a wedding. We didn't invite our photographer, but "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-10-dj4o3",
									"text": "Jennie",
									"marks": [
										"key-9-dopuj"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-11-klsm0",
									"text": ", Laurel's younger sister, was there with her camera, so we have some great photos of the evening (she's a professional photographer).\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-12-suyz5",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_839\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-9-dopuj",
									"href": "http://jenniferbastian.com/home.html"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-13-2t3x9",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207449784_e1b4222688_o.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-15-sr60k",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207449784_e1b4222688_o.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207449784_e1b4222688_o.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-26-c1kec",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-16-hwylm",
									"text": " Jen Gilmour, our officiant and I combine our faces to make what might be my favorite picture of the night.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-17-ocapx",
									"text": "It ended up being great--we ordered pizza from "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-19-s42jy",
									"text": "Roman Candle",
									"marks": [
										"key-18-lxudl"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-20-98f5b",
									"text": " (they had the biggest range of vegetarian choices--we ended up ordering 3 16\" pizzas in 6 different vegetarian varieties, which was incredible), spinach salad from Costco (we bought wayyyyy too much--for a second we forgot that our wedding was going to be in Wisconsin), Laurel bought organic red and white wines from Woodman's (I can't remember the label), and ordered a 1/2 keg of Spotted Cow from "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-22-3l0zf",
									"text": "Party Port",
									"marks": [
										"key-21-hqjnz"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-23-7cjmy",
									"text": " (we ended up using it that evening, leaving it on ice overnight and then bringing it out the next night at the reception--and still had quite a bit left at the end of the evening). It was the first time that I'd ever reserved a keg of anything in my life, so I was glad to have Laurel's step-brothers on hand to tap it and get the libations flowing.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-24-92jks",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_837\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-18-lxudl",
									"href": "http://theromancandle.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/TRC_menu_middleton_2012_04.pdf"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-21-hqjnz",
									"href": "http://www.party-port.com/kegs.htm"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-25-wx19b",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207480818_7e85da52cb_b.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-27-3mvp8",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207480818_7e85da52cb_b.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207480818_7e85da52cb_b.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-32-nvorf",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-28-ddktr",
									"text": " The \"beer gods\"--Laurel's step-brothers Daniel and Patrick Hill, with Jennie Bastian, Laurel's sister in the center.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-29-iwjyq",
									"text": "I'm sure some guests were a little disappointed that we didn't have any animal flesh to consume, but they seemed to hide it well, and everybody looked happy and well fed by the end of the evening.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-30-ir2fm",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_833\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-31-4k11l",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207494506_c683842e91_b.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-33-i41y4",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207494506_c683842e91_b.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207494506_c683842e91_b.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-43-ioxly",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-34-j04dj",
									"text": " Some of the pizza on offer. It was delicious.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-35-jxhb2",
									"text": "We also asked my old college roommates from Awesome City at BYU if they wanted to play some live music (they'd all been in college rock bands in Provo--"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-36-lubnp",
									"text": "Zero to Nothing",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-37-2srdh",
									"text": " and "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-38-kufs5",
									"text": "Vajra",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-39-mdv5z",
									"text": " were the most prominent), which they did for the last hour or so of the party. It was a perfect evening--Laurel and I ate well, mingled and chatted with family and old friends, and all kinds of people met each other for the first time, reacquainted themselves with old friends, and exchanged stories, tall tales, and memories. We had the building reserved for fours hours (from 5-8 pm), but no one came to kick us out, so we ended up staying an extra 2 1/2 hours, laughing and rocking into the night (thanks Eagle Heights!).\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-40-bj3nu",
									"text": "Total rental cost: $60\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-41-gyjhl",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_829\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-42-hbapk",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207444320_26977e41f5_o.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-44-t7qov",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207444320_26977e41f5_o.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207444320_26977e41f5_o.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-48-8i4er",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-45-rn6fn",
									"text": " Jessica Klaers, Sarah Wagstaff, Peter Meulenbroek, Janelle Pulczinski, Maureen Purcell, Colleen Lucey [back row, L-R] behind Laurel and Steel[/caption]There were even a couple of super-cute babies there.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-46-yi4wn",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_831\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-47-qj7xk",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207485114_1a7853110b_b.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-49-0qmyf",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207485114_1a7853110b_b.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207485114_1a7853110b_b.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-54-oppsx",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-50-yphye",
									"text": " Emeline Gardner holding her and Spencer's cute giant BABY Elsa![/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-51-2jtgz",
									"text": "Many of our guests were staying at the nearby Best Western and Inntowner, which offered a free shuttle to and from the pizza party (because the Community Center is within a 2 mile radius from the hotel), so lots of our guests ended up traveling to and from the reception that way, which we were glad for (because they saved gas, had a fun social experience, and kept the roads safe since some of our guests drank alcohol that evening). It looked like a fun ride.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-52-tiwob",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_841\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-53-fnemo",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207495554_89246cc242_b.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-55-dzy5r",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207495554_89246cc242_b.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207495554_89246cc242_b.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-60-qez6e",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-56-ln0dd",
									"text": " My sister Sarah does her Zoolander face on the shuttle.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-57-5vyn7",
									"text": "The Reception:\n",
									"marks": [
										"strong"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-58-l8eul",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_842\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-59-p0qpu",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-421.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-61-xcn6e",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-421.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-421.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-69-rgh0m",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-62-5sp7d",
									"text": " The staff (I think it was Bettye Johnson, but I'm not 100% sure) made a fun welcome sign to greet our guests at the entrance. Unless otherwise noted, all remaining photographs by Sarah Maughan of SLM Photography.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-63-89jji",
									"text": "The reception was obviously a little more complex to plan. As with the wedding itself, we wanted a small, relatively intimate event that would be memorable, personally significant, and consistent with our deepest values and greatest priorities. From the very beginning, Laurel wanted to hold the reception in the "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-65-q6a02",
									"text": "Goodman Community Center",
									"marks": [
										"key-64-4hfrd"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-66-1ksa5",
									"text": ", a fantastic community center in the Atwood neighborhood on Madison's east side.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-67-inh2r",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_843\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-64-4hfrd",
									"href": "http://www.goodmancenter.org/about-center/mission-goals"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-68-inx9z",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-422.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-70-nsfbn",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-422.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-422.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-75-8qtu1",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-71-4x742",
									"text": " The Goodman Center.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-72-vrl3a",
									"text": "In fact, this was the first reservation that we made--Laurel found out what dates the Goodman Center was available, and we planned our wedding around that timing (the main reason we got married on April 21st is because that was a Saturday in the spring where the Goodman Center was available). We did consider a few other locations for the reception, but I don't think we ever really seriously considered holding the reception anywhere but the Goodman Center, one of Laurel's favorite places (and organizations) in town. For the reception, we reserved the Evjue Community Room (where everyone was seated) and Merrill Lynch room (which held the bar, the buffet tables, and the dance floor).\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-73-rama4",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_852\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-74-tptzl",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-440.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-76-29b4n",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-440.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-440.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-80-u9094",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-77-h0sr7",
									"text": " The Evjue community room, viewed from the Merrill Lynch room (there's an easily removable large sliding partition between the rooms that was open all evening for our event).[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-78-sj8y3",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_863\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-79-h8m6j",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-647.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-81-ynz6h",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-647.jpg",
