							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-427.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-427.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-133-ofiqg",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-126-6x2s1",
									"text": " Rows of name cards for table settings. Table numbers were written on the back.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-127-6zh3k",
									"text": "Just inside the reception room, we set up a long table which had our guest book and several pens and colored pencils. For the guest book, I bought a small (8 1/2\" x 6\") solid white "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-129-23vhn",
									"text": "bare book",
									"marks": [
										"key-128-im0k3"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-130-ra9i2",
									"text": " from Artists and Craftsman, and we asked guests to write us a note and draw us a picture. Laurel's cousin Stephanie Hill decorated the front cover for us and we got all kinds of amazing drawings (including cat dancers, microphone pants, flowers, stick figures, wedding tableaux, exploding pies and dancing babies and jackrabbits leading a patriotic dance dance revolution). It was a good guest book. While we didn't make a wedding registry and had asked our guests not to give us unneeded gifts, several of our guests brought cards and other generous offerings, which they left on this table, which also was home to our 'wedding favors'--the gift we wanted to give our guests: wedding poems, a folded letterpressed pamphlet with poems that Laurel and wrote for each other.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-131-d5b9d",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_868\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-128-im0k3",
