							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-200-q9pp9",
									"text": " First dance.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-201-nlhxk",
									"text": "Laurel danced with her father for the second song, The Temptations' classic "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-203-bboe4",
									"text": "\"My Girl\"",
									"marks": [
										"key-202-yahrh"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-204-6rdc2",
									"text": ". Much jauntier--we all laughed and smiled. It was wonderful.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-205-786sz",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_876\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-202-yahrh",
									"href": "http://grooveshark.com/s/My+Girl/2v4W1I?src=5"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-206-zl14b",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-638.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-208-fid1j",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-638.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-638.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-220-gxr22",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-209-wnli6",
									"text": " Laurel and her father dance.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-210-ztzzx",
									"text": "For the third song, my mother and I danced to the Beatles' "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-212-k6inb",
									"text": "\"In My Life.\"",
									"marks": [
										"key-211-pnmp8"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-213-xy2pw",
									"text": " When I was a kid, growing up in Oklahoma, the Beatles' "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-215-7q9r0",
									"text": "1962-1966",
									"marks": [
										"key-214-knjfu",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-216-kbt45",
									"text": " (red album)",
									"marks": [
										"key-214-knjfu"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-217-myxnr",
									"text": " was the first cassette tape I remember listening to in the car, and one of the only albums of music I ever remember my mom really enjoying--during car rides, she tended to prefer silence or very quiet talking (as the mother of four young children, can you really blame her?). Mom danced barefoot. It was great.\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-218-ginr3",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_877\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-211-pnmp8",
									"href": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T3wvUwb4p4Q"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-214-knjfu",
									"href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1962%E2%80%931966"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-219-wa9qy",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-644.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-221-j5kmz",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-644.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-644.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-225-edoa5",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-222-07pqn",
									"text": " I share a dance with mom.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-223-mr0xm",
									"text": "After that, things got real. I wish I had better photographic evidence of it, but the two men in wheelchairs were the most memorable and energetic dancers, breaking all kinds of stereotypes about the elderly and the so-called 'disabled.' Thanks Grandpa and Mattie for rocking the floor so hard (and an honorable mention to the lovely Jean Ellzey, who also wowed more than a few people with her nimble moves. While I may not have great photos of any of them leading the charge, I do have a couple of Laurel, who knows a thing or two about how to move.[caption id=\"attachment_879\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-224-l69en",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207426230_888ec0efaf_o-1.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-226-eepux",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207426230_888ec0efaf_o-1.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/7207426230_888ec0efaf_o-1.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-230-tzj0r",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-227-u5u6y",
									"text": " BOOM! Photo by Jennie Bastian.[/caption]\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-228-a7vfx",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_880\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"500\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-229-gwgaz",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/523036_3507032512908_1184649120_32615796_832037809_n.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-231-9mkgd",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/523036_3507032512908_1184649120_32615796_832037809_n.jpg",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/523036_3507032512908_1184649120_32615796_832037809_n.jpg"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-235-lar2w",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-232-ontaz",
									"text": " Stepping out. Photo by Christine Hill.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-233-e6ni5",
									"text": "After the dancing ended (just before 11pm), we packed up the things we needed to take home (like the leftover cupcakes--hello box freezer!), gave away the lanterns and flowers, and went home. The Goodman Center takes care of final clean up and take down of the room, which was great, and also meant that we were out of the building by 11:45. Great evening, great experience, great venue. We couldn't recommend it more highly as a location for a wedding reception.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-234-ge8hp",
									"text": "Total Rental Cost: I can't remember the exact figure right now--I'll check our records and update this later. I think the building rental was around $800 plus a refundable $500 deposit, and the linens and table setting rental came to $365."
								}
							]
						}
					]
				}
			},
			{
				"id": "posts:one-month-later-introduction-to-the-marriage-posts",
				"slug": "one-month-later-introduction-to-the-marriage-posts",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "One Month Later: Introducing the Wedding Planning Series",
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-10-9h4y8",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-6gd43",
									"text": "Last month, on April 21, I married my best friend "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-3-xebvw",
									"text": "Laurel Bastian",
									"marks": [
										"key-2-vuqjf"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-4-hlcwv",
									"text": " in the presence of our families and a few very close friends. It was the happiest day of my life. We held the ceremony at the "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-6-9z4q4",
									"text": "Gates of Heaven",
									"marks": [
										"key-5-uvqxj"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-7-9hr8x",
									"text": ", a former synagogue now owned and operated by the City of Madison Parks department. The building itself, a beautiful old stone structure, was placed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1970 and moved to its current location in James Madison Park in 1971. Here's what it looks like today:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-8-d3hu9",
									"text": "[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"487\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-2-vuqjf",
									"href": "http://laurelbastian.com/"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-5-uvqxj",
									"href": "http://www.cityofmadison.com/parks/parks/reservableShelter.cfm?id=35"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-9-ybzzo",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-390.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-11-ai69z",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-390.jpg?w=487",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-390.jpg?w=487"
							},
							"alt": "Image of Steel and Laurel in front of the Gates of Heaven"
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-16-c0co6",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-12-b9y69",
									"text": " Gates of Heaven from exterior. Photo by SLM Photography.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-13-qb2ao",
									"text": "Here's a shot of the interior:\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-14-u8kfm",
									"text": "[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"487\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-15-kjm7p",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-129.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-17-wvfwb",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-129.jpg?w=487",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/steel-and-laurel-129.jpg?w=487"
							},
							"alt": "Interior of Gates of Heaven."
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-20-vjr7p",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-18-f4dv4",
									"text": " Interior of Gates of Heaven. Photo by SLM Photography.[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-19-b24zx",
									"text": "I wanted to wait until after our wedding preparations were completed and we had some time to reflect on the ceremony, reception, and overall experience, but now that more than a month has passed, I thought I'd share a series of blog posts detailing some of the choices we made leading up to our wedding. This isn't meant to be a place to brag or an effort to judge or criticize the choices that others have and are making, but a place to describe what we chose to do, why we chose the things we chose, and how we felt about those choices. In part, I write this because it seems that weddings are in the air--Laurel and I are of an age now when many of our peers are marrying or considering marriage--and in part because, quite frankly, we found many components of the marriage industry wholly insane. Our hope is that these posts might be of interest for others who are contemplating marriage or something like it, and are looking for ideas about how to have a memorable, meaningful experience within a fairly limited budget. Here are the posts I have in mind, though if any readers have suggestions or questions, I'd be delighted to alter or expand my plans:"
								}
							]
						},
