								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-30-92mdx",
									"href": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ctTQeTPILI8"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-33-ts0r5",
									"href": "http://whiskeyclone.net/disco/releaseinfo.php?discoID=10"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-36-wtfkg",
									"href": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EkjmjYrVL0g"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-39-o6icw",
									"href": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a6I1HHuUvBg"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-42-pcyy4",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/beck-odelay-portrait.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-44-jh346",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/beck-odelay-portrait.jpg?w=300",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/beck-odelay-portrait.jpg?w=300"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-96-qde63",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-45-zjjfh",
									"text": "In time I started buying Beck's singles, amassing b-sides and alternate recordings, trading bootlegs, and trying to collect rarities and live-only songs he recorded. I generally thought Beck was pretty rad. That feeling grew considerably when he came out with "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-47-9cqs6",
									"text": "Odelay",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-46-fe7h4"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-48-y04yb",
									"text": ", which blew my mind when I first heard it weeks before my 14th birthday. It was the best album I'd ever heard, and I played it almost nonstop for weeks. I was really into old-school rap at the time (think "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-50-sxqzx",
									"text": "Grandmaster Flash",
									"marks": [
										"key-49-vy9b1"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-51-fzp7s",
									"text": " or anything from Sugar Hill Records--I bought their "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-53-6pq9y",
									"text": "boxed set",
									"marks": [
										"key-52-cx90n"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-54-rpx7f",
									"text": " when it came out the next year) and loved the way that Beck moved so fluidly between so many styles and genres, how he did white boy rap so lazily, so funkily, so eccentrically. I saw his performance (in a white suit, natch!) on "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-56-vzgpa",
									"text": "Sessions at West 54th Street",
									"marks": [
										"key-55-xk35a"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-57-r618d",
									"text": " (you have to check out the sick cover of "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-59-0ol2g",
									"text": "Keith Mansfield's ",
									"marks": [
										"key-58-bcm7z"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-60-l8yip",
									"text": "Soul Thing",
									"marks": [
										"key-58-bcm7z",
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-61-mk4sr",
									"text": " ",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-62-mgz41",
									"text": "his band plays as "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-64-o7kh5",
									"text": "his intro",
									"marks": [
										"key-63-z6slg"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-65-j31f8",
									"text": " and their closing number, "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-67-4pa7b",
									"text": "an unbelievable 10-minute long version of Where It's At",
									"marks": [
										"key-66-nszgm"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-68-8mdqf",
									"text": ") and tried to model all my dance moves at Mormon Saturday Night Dances (SNDs) on his performance. A couple years later Beck put out "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-69-6eqrx",
									"text": "Mutations",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-70-46vh5",
									"text": ", a solid, mostly acoustic album that was initially supposed to be come out on K Records as a kind of follow up to One Foot on the Grave, but ended up getting poached by Geffen due to the massive commercial success of "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-71-hfabk",
									"text": "Odelay",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-72-hn8wk",
									"text": ". I liked it a lot, but couldn't help feeling super excited for the album that was supposed to be the proper follow up to "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-73-o8buf",
									"text": "Odelay",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-74-f6uyp",
									"text": ", one that was rumored to have heavy funk influence, one on which Beck morphed into a tongue-in-cheek Prince worshipper, one which I was sure would be awesome.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-75-w02u9",
									"text": "That happened a couple of months into my senior year of high school, when he released "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-77-ucekt",
									"text": "Midnite Vultures",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-76-63zpw"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-78-m9vn0",
									"text": ". To 17-year old me, this album was the greatest thing that could have ever happened, musically speaking. My favorite part of the record was pretty much all of it, but if I had to pick one thing that pushed it over the top it was the release of "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-80-986oi",
									"text": "Debra",
									"marks": [
										"key-79-3v2jc"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-81-k8yy4",
									"text": ", a song that Beck had been performing live for several years in all kinds of various forms and in several funky variations (see "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-83-7apa6",
									"text": "this performance",
									"marks": [
										"key-82-ei5uz"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-84-ezau5",
									"text": " for a taste, and "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-86-jxis0",
									"text": "this one",
									"marks": [
										"key-85-2aah5"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-87-605xx",
									"text": " for dessert) but which had never made it on to any of his albums. I have never seen Beck live--one of my greatest musical regrets, particularly since I might have seen the dude in the cape doing something crazyawesome like all the stuff he does in "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-89-s8cb3",
									"text": "this video",
									"marks": [
										"key-88-l4xnb"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-90-gkg1v",
									"text": "--but I will say in my defense that I haven't had many reasonable opportunities to do so. Despite Beck's crazy touring schedule in the late 90's and early 00's, he didn't play any shows in Oklahoma until after I had already moved to Idaho, and the closest he came to Boise while I was living there was "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-92-c2acw",
									"text": "a show",
									"marks": [
										"key-91-mo6an"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-93-dogfj",
									"text": " in Salt Lake City in April 2000. He played three shows in 2008 in Chicago while I was living in Madison, but I didn't make it to any of those, and he's not touring much these days. Despite having never seen Beck myself, when I was a teenager the brother-in-law of my high school girlfriend gave me a pale blue Beck t-shirt from an early tour (thanks Jared Williams!) that I wore on special occasions, mostly when I needed to look especially awesome. I've still got it in a drawer, awaiting the day when I finally see the man live and in person.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-94-mwkkm",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_110\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\" caption=\"Still from \"Sexx Laws\" video shoot set. Jack Black on left, Neil Strauss in center, Justin Meldal-Johnsen on right.\"]"
								}
							],
