				}
			},
			{
				"id": "posts:on-earth-day",
				"slug": "on-earth-day",
				"status": "published",
				"data": {
					"title": "On Earth Day",
					"featured_image": {
						"provider": "external",
						"id": "",
						"src": "https://steelwagstaff.info/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/earth_day_celebration.jpg"
					},
					"content": [
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-3-xit87",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-1-2ok1g",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_98\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\" caption=\"Gaylord Nelson\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-2-30aom",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/gaylord_nelson.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-4-f5g07",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/gaylord_nelson.jpg?w=300",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/gaylord_nelson.jpg?w=300"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-29-egvxp",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-5-nei3j",
									"text": "[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-6-5wj8g",
									"text": "Today is the 41st annual Earth Day, one of my favorite days of the year. Today I want to tell part of the story of its origins, its importance, and why I treasure the values that underlie its celebration and observance.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-7-i34ml",
									"text": "Earth Day is the child of former Wisconsin Senator "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-9-n18xi",
									"text": "Gaylord Nelson",
									"marks": [
										"key-8-sc3vs"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-10-feeu7",
									"text": " (see additional bios "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-12-311s5",
									"text": "here",
									"marks": [
										"key-11-rjli9"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-13-oev45",
									"text": " and "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-15-2udm8",
									"text": "here",
									"marks": [
										"key-14-b0lhp"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-16-kylzz",
									"text": "). In 1962, Nelson, then in the last year of his first term as Governor of Wisconsin, won election (as a Democrat) to the United States Senate, defeating 78 year old "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-18-o3i3c",
									"text": "Alexander Wiley",
									"marks": [
										"key-17-90t8q"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-19-6fdek",
									"text": ", a four-term Senator who was, at the time, the longest tenured Republican in the Senate. According to "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-21-61qrs",
									"text": "David",
									"marks": [
										"key-20-idzd1"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-22-y7q14",
									"text": " "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-24-1a94a",
									"text": "Webber",
									"marks": [
										"key-23-kfnhk"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-25-tat8i",
									"text": ", a political science professor at the University of Missouri, Nelson had gained prominence during his term as governor for his enthusiastic and innovative support for environmental and conservation issues. Webber "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-27-mccgn",
									"text": "writes",
									"marks": [
										"key-26-udim8"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-28-glaei",
									"text": ":"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-8-sc3vs",
									"href": "http://www.nelsonearthday.net/nelson/index.htm"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-11-rjli9",
									"href": "http://wilderness.org/content/gaylord-nelson"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-14-b0lhp",
									"href": "http://digicoll.library.wisc.edu/cgi/f/findaid/findaid-idx?c=wiarchives;view=reslist;subview=standard;didno=uw-whs-mss01020;focusrgn=bioghist;cc=wiarchives;byte=185621835"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-17-90t8q",
									"href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Wiley"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-20-idzd1",
									"href": "http://politicalscience.missouri.edu/people/webber.html"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-23-kfnhk",
									"href": "http://web.missouri.edu/~webberd/"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-26-udim8",
									"href": "http://web.missouri.edu/~webberd/Nelson.html"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-31-ntg82",
							"style": "blockquote",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-30-az8ql",
									"text": "In the late 1950s, a crucial issues facing Wisconsin was the great demand for outdoor recreation. A 1959 study found that over 25 percent of Chicago residents took an over-night vacation trip to Wisconsin. Governor Nelson proposed a bold plan to expand the state's conservation efforts. In August 1961, Nelson won legislative approval in 1961 of the Outdoor Resources Action Program financed by a one-cent-per-pack cigarette tax to fund the state acquisition of parks and wetlands. This 10-year program used \"conservation easements\" to purchase land rights to private property. Instead of actually buying the land, a conservation easements pays the property owner to preserve land as wilderness. The Outdoor Resources Action Program provided for recreation areas throughout the state for use as wildlife areas and public parks. While governor, Nelson proposed other environmental measure such as regulating detergents that were making their way to Wisconsin's rivers and streams."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-38-wlb22",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-32-q9djr",
									"text": "Nelson carried this concern for environmental issues directly into his new role as a US Senator. In an "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-34-dyg6g",
									"text": "article",
									"marks": [
										"key-33-rw9cx"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-35-waqr2",
									"text": " he wrote for "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-36-ej6g4",
									"text": "American Heritage Magazine ",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-37-hzu9k",
									"text": "in 1993, Nelson revealed that the idea for Earth Day"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-33-rw9cx",
									"href": "http://earthday.envirolink.org/history.html"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-41-pxpmk",
							"style": "blockquote",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-39-lsio5",
									"text": "evolved over a period of seven years starting in 1962. For several years, it had been troubling me that the state of our environment was simply a non-issue in the politics of the country. Finally, in November 1962, an idea occurred to me that was, I thought, a virtual cinch to put the environment into the political \"limelight\" once and for all. The idea was to persuade President Kennedy to give visibility to this issue by going on a national conservation tour. I flew to Washington to discuss the proposal with Attorney General Robert Kennedy, who liked the idea. So did the President. The President began his five-day, eleven-state conservation tour in September 1963. For many reasons the tour did not succeed in putting the issue onto the national political agenda.  ...\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-40-lpvtv",
									"text": "After President Kennedy's tour, I still hoped for some idea that would thrust the environment into the political mainstream. Six years would pass before the idea that became Earth Day occurred to me while on a conservation speaking tour out West in the summer of 1969. At the time, anti-Vietnam War demonstrations, called \"teach-ins,\" had spread to college campuses all across the nation. Suddenly, the idea occurred to me - why not organize a huge grassroots protest over what was happening to our environment?"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-43-1mz20",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-42-ncru3",
									"text": "Nelson did organize these teach ins, they were wildly successful, and in September of 1969, at a conference in Seattle, Nelson announced his plans for nationwide grassroots demonstrations in the following spring on behalf of the environment. These events would be coordinated to take place on April 22, 1970 and would be known as Earth Day. Following this announcement, Nelson remembers"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-45-i5od2",
							"style": "blockquote",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-44-c5e8r",
									"text": "The response was electric. It took off like gangbusters. Telegrams, letters, and telephone inquiries poured in from all across the country. The American people finally had a forum to express its concern about what was happening to the land, rivers, lakes, and air - and they did so with spectacular exuberance. For the next four months, two members of my Senate staff, Linda Billings and John Heritage, managed Earth Day affairs out of my Senate office."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-61-ymf29",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-46-txl3x",
									"text": "Aided in part by the appearance of a "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-48-ar5gz",
									"text": "lengthy front page feature",
									"marks": [
										"key-47-zjke3"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-49-cv9p5",
									"text": " by Gladwin Hill in the November 30, 1969 issue of NY Times on the rise of environmental activism on college campuses around the country, Nelson quickly discovered that \"grassroots activities had ballooned beyond the capacity of my U.S. Senate office staff to keep up with the telephone calls, paper work, inquiries, etc. In mid-January, three months before Earth Day, John Gardner, Founder of Common Cause, provided temporary space for a Washington, D.C. headquarters.\" Nelson appointed twenty-five year old "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-51-72wwj",
									"text": "Denis",
									"marks": [
										"key-50-y68rn"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-52-8vtzb",
									"text": " "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-54-a9v86",
									"text": "Hayes",
									"marks": [
										"key-53-pp29j"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-55-2kvhu",
									"text": " as coordinator of activities and staffed the office with college students. On April 21st, the evening before the schedule Earth Day celebrations, Nelson addressed an audience in the Cooley Auditorium of Milwaukee Technical College and laid out his environmental vision in a compelling and inspiring fashion. You can see video of this speech "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-57-gluwd",
									"text": "here",
									"marks": [
										"key-56-7sreo"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-58-vlx69",
									"text": ".\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-59-jrb8k",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_96\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"174\" caption=\"The Earth Day issue of the Gaylord Nelson Newsletter\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-47-zjke3",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/earth_day.pdf"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-50-y68rn",
									"href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denis_Hayes"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-53-pp29j",
									"href": "http://www.nrdc.org/reference/profiles/prohayes.asp"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-56-7sreo",
									"href": "http://www.nelsonearthday.net/video/vha593_nelsonearthday.htm"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-60-qd2pg",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/earth_day_newsletter.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-62-fqxdb",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/earth_day_newsletter.jpg?w=174",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/earth_day_newsletter.jpg?w=174"
							},
							"alt": "Front page of Gaylord Nelson Newsletter announcing First Earth Day"
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-65-1zq49",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-63-bhpch",
									"text": "[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-64-96en9",
									"text": "The following day millions of people gathered across the United States to advocate on behalf of their environmental concerns and to express their love of the planet and their desire that we (and our governments, businesses, and other institutions) do more to protect, preserve, and improve its health. The first Earth Day was a massive success, and in the 40+ years since it's first observance, it has become a global phenomenon, uniting people across many cultures, languages, and backgrounds in the common cause of greater care for our shared planet, deeper awareness of pressing environmental and social concerns, and conversations about possible ways to repair the damage we have wrought upon the Earth. In his 1993 reflections on the origins of Earth Day Nelson asserted that in his opinion the first Earth Day was so wildly successful"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-67-srqkz",
							"style": "blockquote",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-66-t1ac0",
									"text": "because of the spontaneous response at the grassroots level. We had neither the time nor resources to organize 20 million demonstrators and the thousands of schools and local communities that participated. That was the remarkable thing about Earth Day. It organized itself."
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-108-cua17",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-68-l43z6",
									"text": "I love this story and the possibility that it holds out for similar action in our time and generations from now.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-69-ulr5d",
									"text": "If you're curious to know more about Gaylord Nelson or Earth Day, I have three recommendations. The first is this fantastic Nelson Institute for Environmental Studies "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-71-srq3n",
									"text": "site",
									"marks": [
										"key-70-kaxns"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-72-1jyv2",
									"text": ", which has outstanding pages devoted to Nelson's "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-74-r7qw1",
									"text": "life story",
									"marks": [
										"key-73-cwuis"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-75-7n3vv",
									"text": " as well as"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-77-6rrq8",
									"text": " the story of Earth Day",
									"marks": [
										"key-76-is037"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-78-45c2f",
									"text": ". This very impressive and incredibly informative site was built through the collaborative efforts of history Ph.D. student Brian Hamilton (whom I first met as a fellow student in a seminar led by Bill Cronon in which we helped build this "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-80-cxfdk",
									"text": "Learning Historical Research",
									"marks": [
										"key-79-hqa4g"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-81-ckw8b",
									"text": " site), webmaster Melanie McCalmont of "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-83-rmyg5",
									"text": "Synchronous Publications",
									"marks": [
										"key-82-m24e4"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-84-nji2f",
									"text": ", UW Professors "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-86-wu6r3",
									"text": "Gregg Mitman",
									"marks": [
										"key-85-1yxrk"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-87-cjywe",
									"text": " and "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-89-noaz3",
									"text": "Bill Cronon",
									"marks": [
										"key-88-q0oss"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-90-j5fov",
									"text": ", and consulting scholar "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-92-v03ir",
									"text": "Adam Rome",
									"marks": [
										"key-91-yttvq"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-93-0t0o1",
									"text": ", who is currently at work on a book about Earth Day, which will published later this year by Hill & Wang. You can get lost in here and spend days or weeks immersed in rich, exciting, and deeply interesting material.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-94-kzxsu",
									"text": "I'd also recommend the PBS American Experience film "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-95-p2a4b",
									"text": "Earth Days",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-96-qhs3o",
									"text": ", which you can "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-98-o60qw",
									"text": "watch",
									"marks": [
										"key-97-spwi1"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-99-6qyos",
									"text": " (or read the "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-101-k2uhd",
									"text": "transcript",
									"marks": [
										"key-100-f7cog"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-102-nyjh9",
									"text": ") from their website. The site also includes a host of supporting materials, including a "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-104-s1nm4",
									"text": "teacher's guide",
									"marks": [
										"key-103-6tr4f"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-105-9k55z",
									"text": ".\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-106-vpi11",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_95\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\" caption=\"Earth Day Celebration in Burlington, Wisconsin, 1973.\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
