						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-135-8gfsh",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-110-2lhms",
									"text": "[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-111-bl439",
									"text": "The other recommendation I'd make would be checking out some of the "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-113-qc5pe",
									"text": "primary historical documents",
									"marks": [
										"key-112-ux659"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-114-8w8vl",
									"text": " collected by "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-116-1eof5",
									"text": "The Wisconsin Historical Society",
									"marks": [
										"key-115-bxvpb"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-117-a2h12",
									"text": ". In addition to housing the incredible "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-119-2ok07",
									"text": "Gaylord Nelson Papers, 1954-2006 collection",
									"marks": [
										"key-118-rb6dx"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-120-yk6ja",
									"text": ", the WHS has collected an enormous number of documents related to Nelson and his "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-122-554rp",
									"text": "early Earth Day plans",
									"marks": [
										"key-121-qcjx7"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-123-fcunb",
									"text": ", including "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-125-jtmj9",
									"text": "this newsletter",
									"marks": [
										"key-124-cijws"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-126-ddpf8",
									"text": " announcing Nelson's plans for the enviromental teach-ins described in the quote above and "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-128-5nf0x",
									"text": "this newsletter",
									"marks": [
										"key-127-igj4f"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-129-zzkp1",
									"text": " announcing the successes of the first Earth Day Celebration on April 22, 1970 and heralding the beginning of a new \"mass movement\". My favorite detail? It contains this nugget: the first Earth Day in Madison, Wisconsin was observed \"at sunrise over Lake Mendota with a Sanskrit invocation and a reading of the last chapter of the Book of Genesis [presumably "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-131-dn9de",
									"text": "Genesis 50",
									"marks": [
										"key-130-4ez5j"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-132-lg2c4",
									"text": "] with an apology to God for man's assaults on the landscape.\" Who knew?\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-133-gdolv",
									"text": "[caption id=\"attachment_97\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\" caption=\"Two of my heroes, Gaylord Nelson and Stewart Udall\"]"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-112-ux659",
									"href": "http://www.wisconsinhistory.org/dictionary/index.asp?action=view&term_id=1849"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-115-bxvpb",
									"href": "http://www.wisconsinhistory.org/about/"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-118-rb6dx",
									"href": "http://digicoll.library.wisc.edu/cgi/f/findaid/findaid-idx?c=wiarchives;view=reslist;subview=standard;didno=uw-whs-mss01020;focusrgn=bioghist;cc=wiarchives;byte=185621835"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-121-qcjx7",
									"href": "http://www.wisconsinhistory.org/turningpoints/search.asp?id=1671"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-124-cijws",
									"href": "http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm4/document.php?CISOROOT=/tp&CISOPTR=50429&CISOSHOW=50416"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-127-igj4f",
									"href": "http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm4/document.php?CISOROOT=/tp&CISOPTR=49118&CISOSHOW=49116"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-130-4ez5j",
									"href": "http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Genesis+50&version=KJV"
								},
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-134-6g5dw",
									"href": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/gaylord_nelson_stewart_udall.jpg"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "image",
							"_key": "key-136-fp0gs",
							"asset": {
								"_type": "reference",
								"_ref": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/gaylord_nelson_stewart_udall.jpg?w=300",
								"url": "http://steelwagstaff.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/gaylord_nelson_stewart_udall.jpg?w=300"
							},
							"alt": ""
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-160-iqydi",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-137-2dh5e",
									"text": "[/caption]\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-138-3kdci",
									"text": "So, more than 4o years on, what does Earth Day mean today? What ought we to be demonstrating about, protesting against, advocating for, rejoicing over? Twenty years ago, Nelson himself tried to answer the question in a "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-140-60111",
									"text": "statement at the Madison Beyond War Ceremony",
									"marks": [
										"key-139-grg4d"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-141-11me9",
									"text": ".  ",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-142-kqp8m",
									"text": "Last year, Ruth Conniff, political editor at "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-144-avy5z",
									"text": "The Progressive",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-143-lj5sv"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-145-ezqf3",
									"text": ", ",
									"marks": [
										"em"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-146-ufntk",
									"text": "offered "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-148-3lmn9",
									"text": "some thoughts",
									"marks": [
										"key-147-4jlc1"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-149-dnm42",
									"text": " on this question, and this year, Maude Barlow and Shannon Biggs have shared "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-151-sattd",
									"text": "their ideas",
									"marks": [
										"key-150-0eery"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-152-lav17",
									"text": " in the same publication.\n\n"
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-153-42qdx",
									"text": "My feelings on this question are numerous. I love the earth, and want it to be healthy. I want to do my part to honor, celebrate, and respect the environment in the places that I inhabit, as well as the places which are affected by the products that I consume--those regions of the earth which are directly affected by my presence on earth and the choices I make as a human actor. In honor of Earth Day, I'm wearing green, pledging publicly to be more vocal in my support of wise environmental policies and better consumer decisions in the coming year (and beyond), and planning to join several of my friends this evening at the opening of Heather Swan's gorgeous art exhibit: "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-155-tshkq",
									"text": "Loss, Longing, and Belonging: Inhabiting the Human Body in an Endangered World",
									"marks": [
										"key-154-yyv47"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-156-21i5o",
									"text": ", sponsored by the "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-158-5rncz",
									"text": "Center for Culture, History, and the Environment",
									"marks": [
										"key-157-ds56k"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-159-4xri4",
									"text": ". What are you doing for the earth and its many inhabitants this Earth Day?"
								}
							],
							"markDefs": [
								{
									"_type": "link",
									"_key": "key-139-grg4d",
									"href": "http://www.nelsonearthday.net/collection/fighting-on/nelson_230-11_beyond_war_speech_8Dec90.pdf"
								},
								{
