						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-125-0d23l",
							"style": "blockquote",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-124-31396",
									"text": "“If the health reformers are looking to get the biggest ‘bang for their buck’ both in the prevention and management of chronic disease,” they wrote, “they need look no further than delivering [integrative medicine’s] four pillars [of social, psychological, physical, and environmental health].”"
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"_type": "block",
							"_key": "key-148-8844f",
							"style": "normal",
							"children": [
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-126-vvfv8",
									"text": "The identification of these four pillars of health seem prescient and wise (they seem to me to echo the concerns articulated in Murray Bookchin's theory of "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-128-0kut7",
									"text": "social ecology",
									"marks": [
										"key-127-9ozsg"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-129-e1i3q",
									"text": ", as well as the appeals made by many environmental justice advocates, like "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-131-gqs7w",
									"text": "Majora",
									"marks": [
										"key-130-w4rjs"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-132-rsnrk",
									"text": " "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-134-zwc4j",
									"text": "Carter",
									"marks": [
										"key-133-9r2my"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-135-m82ci",
									"text": ", "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-137-ca2zv",
									"text": "Van",
									"marks": [
										"key-136-okmh8"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-138-mcrct",
									"text": " "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-140-wtpyy",
									"text": "Jones",
									"marks": [
										"key-139-gxxqa"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-141-nuwy5",
									"text": " (the man who served briefly as Obama's Green Jobs champion) or the group "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-143-cyzsw",
									"text": "Green for All",
									"marks": [
										"key-142-jubsi"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-144-cofl3",
									"text": ", to name just a few examples). It also reminds me of Hans-Georg Gadamer's remarkable book "
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-146-7pkr6",
									"text": "The Enigma of Health: the Art of Healing in a Scientific Age",
									"marks": [
										"em",
										"key-145-btieu"
									]
								},
								{
									"_type": "span",
									"_key": "key-147-1a3tv",
									"text": ". But more than any literary or intellectual references, it reminds me of my conversations with my youngest sister, of the idea of an inescapable calling, of that band of a dozen-plus carers in that small Mormon ward in Sheffield England, and of the possibility that we might ourselves accept some kind of responsibility \"for looking after the vulnerable\" who surround us, whose health, surely, is bound up with our own."
								}
							],
